00:00:11.803 --> 00:00:14.339 position:7% line:83% align:start
[MAKISHIMA, KOGAMI] "As though
we are atop living stilts

00:00:14.373 --> 00:00:16.674 position:16% line:89% align:start
which continuously grow,

00:00:16.707 --> 00:00:20.044 position:13% line:83% align:start
occasionally towering over
even church belfries,

00:00:20.079 --> 00:00:25.049 position:13% line:83% align:start
until eventually, walking
becomes difficult and dangerous.

00:00:25.084 --> 00:00:28.052 position:16% line:89% align:start
And at last, they fall."

00:00:29.354 --> 00:00:30.721 position:41% line:83% align:start
[SEM]
They're coming.

00:00:36.095 --> 00:00:39.264 position:16% line:83% align:start
[SEM] Three clicks left,
four clicks right.

00:00:41.166 --> 00:00:44.236 position:19% line:83% align:start
[SEM] One click left,
two clicks right.

00:00:47.038 --> 00:00:48.039 position:44% line:89% align:start
Now.

00:00:49.807 --> 00:00:51.310 position:41% line:83% align:start
[SEM]
You did it, Kogami.

00:01:01.752 --> 00:01:04.323 position:13% line:83% align:start
[MAKISHIMA, KOGAMI] "I say
that the cruel law of art

00:01:04.356 --> 00:01:06.425 position:21% line:89% align:start
is that beings die,

00:01:06.458 --> 00:01:08.893 position:7% line:89% align:start
and that we ourselves must die

00:01:08.926 --> 00:01:11.796 position:30% line:83% align:start
after we have
exhausted suffering,

00:01:11.829 --> 00:01:16.235 position:13% line:83% align:start
so that the grass, not of
oblivion but of eternal life,

00:01:16.268 --> 00:01:20.671 position:33% line:83% align:start
should grow,
fertilized by works."

00:01:43.728 --> 00:01:45.297 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SAMRIN]
Do an equipment check.

00:01:52.003 --> 00:01:53.804 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SAMRIN]
How are the glasses?

00:01:57.309 --> 00:02:00.412 position:13% line:83% align:start
All right, I'm downloading
the map and itinerary.

00:02:02.980 --> 00:02:05.417 position:44% line:83% align:start
[MA]
No problems. They're working.

00:02:08.086 --> 00:02:12.157 position:10% line:83% align:start
[SAMRIN] Don't deviate from
the specified route. Let's go.

00:02:53.030 --> 00:02:58.303 position:16% line:89% align:start
[indistinct chattering]

00:03:05.444 --> 00:03:10.482 position:33% line:89% align:start
[dog barks]

00:03:20.592 --> 00:03:25.264 position:35% line:89% align:start
[ringing]

00:03:25.297 --> 00:03:27.266 position:13% line:89% align:start
You have something for me?

00:03:30.435 --> 00:03:31.203 position:35% line:83% align:start
[MIYAZAKI]
Well, my friend,

00:03:31.236 --> 00:03:33.838 position:27% line:83% align:start
I'm glad to see
you in one piece.

00:03:34.972 --> 00:03:36.841 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SAMRIN]
Identity confirmed.

00:03:39.311 --> 00:03:41.480 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SAMRIN]
So. You're Mr. Miyazaki.

00:03:41.513 --> 00:03:44.182 position:16% line:83% align:start
[MIYAZAKI] That's right.
But turnabout's fair play.

00:03:44.216 --> 00:03:46.184 position:16% line:89% align:start
I gotta check you, too.

00:03:49.354 --> 00:03:51.989 position:13% line:89% align:start
All right. Say something.

00:03:52.023 --> 00:03:53.991 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SAMRIN]
We need a car.

00:03:54.025 --> 00:03:55.860 position:30% line:83% align:start
[WATCH DEVICE]
Identity confirmed.

00:03:55.893 --> 00:03:59.298 position:33% line:83% align:start
There we go.
Let's talk business.

00:03:59.331 --> 00:04:02.267 position:7% line:83% align:start
[SAMRIN] Like I said earlier:
I want an older model car.

00:04:02.301 --> 00:04:05.270 position:16% line:83% align:start
The kind produced before
interior cameras were standard.

00:04:05.304 --> 00:04:07.272 position:30% line:83% align:start
And I want its
biometric systems hacked

00:04:07.306 --> 00:04:10.108 position:10% line:89% align:start
so they show the wrong data.

00:04:10.142 --> 00:04:11.343 position:35% line:83% align:start
[MIYAZAKI]
No problem, boys.

00:04:11.376 --> 00:04:14.912 position:10% line:83% align:start
So long as you fork over the
cash, your wish is my command.

00:04:24.256 --> 00:04:25.956 position:27% line:83% align:start
Cars are clean,
but don't forget.

00:04:25.990 --> 00:04:28.260 position:5% line:89% align:start
You still have street scanners.

00:04:28.293 --> 00:04:30.095 position:21% line:83% align:start
That's a tip for ya,
since you don't strike me

00:04:30.128 --> 00:04:32.597 position:19% line:83% align:start
as a type of guy with
a clear Psycho-Pass.

00:04:38.170 --> 00:04:40.539 position:16% line:83% align:start
[MIKA] I'm surprised you
found out about this.

00:04:40.572 --> 00:04:43.342 position:13% line:83% align:start
I have information brokers
keep me in the loop.

00:04:45.210 --> 00:04:47.145 position:41% line:83% align:start
[MIKA]
Oh.

00:04:47.179 --> 00:04:50.349 position:10% line:83% align:start
That's like what they do in
those old detective movies, huh?

00:05:31.323 --> 00:05:33.525 position:24% line:83% align:start
What you should be
seeing on your devices

00:05:33.558 --> 00:05:35.926 position:10% line:89% align:start
is intel from the pill bug.

00:05:35.960 --> 00:05:38.063 position:19% line:83% align:start
This gang has entered
Japan illegally,

00:05:38.096 --> 00:05:40.030 position:7% line:89% align:start
but I haven't figured out how.

00:05:40.065 --> 00:05:42.234 position:19% line:83% align:start
I count six foreigners
and a Japanese man

00:05:42.267 --> 00:05:44.369 position:24% line:83% align:start
who may be a black
market gun runner.

00:05:44.403 --> 00:05:47.372 position:16% line:83% align:start
A basic Hue check raised
red flags on all of them.

00:05:47.406 --> 00:05:50.208 position:7% line:83% align:start
So I'm pretty sure if we were
to scan them with our Dominators

00:05:50.242 --> 00:05:53.010 position:5% line:89% align:start
we'd get the exact same results.

00:05:53.043 --> 00:05:55.514 position:30% line:83% align:start
So, what's our
engagement plan, then?

00:05:55.547 --> 00:05:58.417 position:16% line:83% align:start
First, we use Drones to
block the parking lot entrance.

00:05:58.450 --> 00:05:59.584 position:10% line:89% align:start
Then we split into two teams

00:05:59.618 --> 00:06:03.020 position:10% line:83% align:start
and use the emergency stairs
and elevator to go under.

00:06:04.021 --> 00:06:05.190 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Scans have already confirmed

00:06:05.223 --> 00:06:08.593 position:7% line:83% align:start
there aren't any traps waiting
for us at either entrance.

00:06:08.627 --> 00:06:11.329 position:24% line:83% align:start
So, Mister Ginoza
and Ms. Kunizuka

00:06:11.363 --> 00:06:14.599 position:21% line:83% align:start
will go with me and
enter from the stairs.

00:06:14.633 --> 00:06:18.236 position:7% line:83% align:start
As for you, Inspector. Put two
Drones in the lead position,

00:06:18.270 --> 00:06:21.972 position:10% line:83% align:start
then enter from the elevator
with Sugo and Hinakawa.

00:06:22.006 --> 00:06:23.642 position:41% line:83% align:start
[MIKA]
Roger that.

00:06:23.675 --> 00:06:25.610 position:21% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] My team will
make the first move.

00:06:25.644 --> 00:06:28.547 position:16% line:83% align:start
We'll use flash grenades
and then charge in,

00:06:28.580 --> 00:06:30.715 position:21% line:83% align:start
putting all of their
attention on us.

00:06:30.749 --> 00:06:31.650 position:24% line:89% align:start
At the same time,

00:06:31.683 --> 00:06:33.984 position:21% line:83% align:start
Team Shimotsuki will
come from the back.

00:06:34.018 --> 00:06:35.520 position:27% line:83% align:start
This way we can
attack on both sides

00:06:35.554 --> 00:06:38.457 position:21% line:83% align:start
and hopefully arrest
them in one fell swoop.

00:06:39.691 --> 00:06:41.226 position:41% line:83% align:start
[SUGO]
Flash grenades, huh?

00:06:41.259 --> 00:06:43.695 position:16% line:83% align:start
That's a pretty cautious
move, Inspector.

00:06:43.728 --> 00:06:45.664 position:21% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] According to
the pill bug's report,

00:06:45.697 --> 00:06:48.633 position:19% line:83% align:start
they're heavily armed
with automatic rifles.

00:06:48.667 --> 00:06:50.268 position:66% line:89% align:start
So then...

00:06:50.302 --> 00:06:52.270 position:27% line:83% align:start
If they're able
to counter-attack,

00:06:52.304 --> 00:06:55.106 position:19% line:83% align:start
it's likely that some
of us will be injured.

00:06:55.140 --> 00:06:57.676 position:13% line:89% align:start
Move with extreme caution.

00:06:57.709 --> 00:06:59.444 position:38% line:83% align:start
[GROUP]
Yes, ma'am.

00:07:02.681 --> 00:07:06.084 position:24% line:89% align:start
[MIYAZAKI humming]

00:07:09.254 --> 00:07:13.023 position:5% line:83% align:start
[MIYAZAKI] Well, it's all there.
Our deal is officially closed.

00:07:17.496 --> 00:07:18.497 position:27% line:89% align:start
[SAMRIN grunts]

00:07:20.565 --> 00:07:21.766 position:35% line:83% align:start
[MIYAZAKI]
What?

00:07:38.750 --> 00:07:42.019 position:35% line:83% align:start
[MIYAZAKI]
Shit. The Public Safety Bureau.

00:07:50.195 --> 00:07:51.830 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
CID!

00:07:51.863 --> 00:07:54.699 position:5% line:89% align:start
Drop your weapons and surrender!

00:07:54.733 --> 00:07:57.302 position:33% line:83% align:start
[DOMINATOR]
Crime Coefficient over 170.

00:07:57.335 --> 00:07:59.371 position:21% line:83% align:start
Suspect is a target
for enforcement.

00:07:59.404 --> 00:08:01.406 position:10% line:89% align:start
Trigger safety now released.

00:08:02.407 --> 00:08:03.475 position:24% line:89% align:start
[MIYAZAKI grunts]

00:08:05.610 --> 00:08:07.212 position:33% line:89% align:start
Return fire!

00:08:16.187 --> 00:08:19.624 position:21% line:83% align:start
Who are these guys?
They fight like soldiers.

00:08:32.404 --> 00:08:34.606 position:33% line:83% align:start
[DOMINATOR]
Crime Coefficient: 310.

00:08:34.639 --> 00:08:38.577 position:16% line:83% align:start
Suspect is a target for
enforcement. Lethal eliminator.

00:08:38.610 --> 00:08:41.212 position:10% line:89% align:start
[TERRORIST grunts, screams]

00:08:48.720 --> 00:08:54.459 position:27% line:89% align:start
[BOTH grunting]

00:08:54.492 --> 00:08:57.529 position:33% line:83% align:start
[DOMINATOR]
Crime Coefficient: 326.

00:08:57.562 --> 00:08:58.697 position:24% line:89% align:start
Lethal eliminator.

00:08:58.730 --> 00:09:00.231 position:21% line:89% align:start
[groans] Son of a--

00:09:00.265 --> 00:09:02.334 position:33% line:83% align:start
[DOMINATOR]
Enforcement action required.

00:09:10.375 --> 00:09:13.278 position:21% line:89% align:start
[MIYAZAKI groaning]

00:09:19.250 --> 00:09:20.318 position:24% line:89% align:start
[TERRORIST grunts]

00:09:27.826 --> 00:09:28.827 position:27% line:89% align:start
[SAMRIN grunts]

00:09:30.929 --> 00:09:32.163 position:33% line:89% align:start
[BOTH grunt]

00:09:35.634 --> 00:09:36.701 position:33% line:89% align:start
[BOTH grunt]

00:09:42.974 --> 00:09:44.242 position:27% line:89% align:start
[GINOZA grunts]

00:09:47.679 --> 00:09:50.415 position:10% line:83% align:start
[DOMINATOR] Target's Threat
Judgment has been reappraised.

00:09:50.448 --> 00:09:53.451 position:5% line:89% align:start
Explosives. Destroy Decomposer.

00:10:00.859 --> 00:10:05.263 position:27% line:89% align:start
[SAMRIN panting]

00:10:10.001 --> 00:10:11.436 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Arrest him!

00:10:11.469 --> 00:10:12.804 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KUNIZUKA]
Roger!

00:10:12.837 --> 00:10:14.906 position:7% line:83% align:start
[KOMISSA] This is the Criminal
Investigation Department

00:10:14.939 --> 00:10:16.975 position:30% line:89% align:start
of the MWPSB.

00:10:17.008 --> 00:10:19.577 position:27% line:83% align:start
Please stop all
resistance immediately.

00:10:19.611 --> 00:10:23.281 position:13% line:83% align:start
Hand over your weapons to
complete your safe surrender.

00:10:23.314 --> 00:10:24.215 position:33% line:83% align:start
This is the
Criminal Investigation--

00:10:24.249 --> 00:10:25.450 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
It's over!

00:10:32.891 --> 00:10:35.326 position:24% line:83% align:start
Drop your weapon.
Put your hands up.

00:10:39.664 --> 00:10:42.367 position:5% line:89% align:start
Turn around slowly and face me.

00:10:47.939 --> 00:10:48.873 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE grunts]

00:10:48.907 --> 00:10:49.708 position:41% line:89% align:start
Don't!

00:10:49.741 --> 00:10:52.711 position:33% line:83% align:start
[DOMINATOR]
Crime Coefficient: 293.

00:10:52.744 --> 00:10:54.913 position:10% line:89% align:start
Enforcement action required.

00:10:57.382 --> 00:10:59.484 position:24% line:89% align:start
[electronic pulse]

00:11:13.364 --> 00:11:14.432 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:13:26.865 --> 00:13:28.666 position:19% line:83% align:start
[KASEI] You took out a
group of armed criminals

00:13:28.700 --> 00:13:31.703 position:16% line:83% align:start
without you or your team
suffering any injuries.

00:13:31.736 --> 00:13:32.604 position:35% line:89% align:start
Good work.

00:13:32.637 --> 00:13:33.872 position:24% line:89% align:start
The target I hit.

00:13:33.905 --> 00:13:36.741 position:7% line:83% align:start
We'll interview him once he's
recovered from the paralyzer.

00:13:36.774 --> 00:13:38.543 position:27% line:89% align:start
Do you approve?

00:13:38.576 --> 00:13:40.011 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KASEI]
That's fine.

00:13:40.044 --> 00:13:42.647 position:13% line:89% align:start
Until then, take it easy.

00:13:42.680 --> 00:13:45.950 position:16% line:83% align:start
A group of heavily-armed
criminals are here illegally.

00:13:45.984 --> 00:13:48.120 position:7% line:89% align:start
All wearing advanced glasses.

00:13:48.153 --> 00:13:51.022 position:5% line:83% align:start
Based on what we've confiscated,
someone with complete knowledge

00:13:51.055 --> 00:13:53.725 position:16% line:83% align:start
of our security systems
helped develop them.

00:13:53.758 --> 00:13:55.526 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KASEI]
Your point being?

00:13:55.560 --> 00:14:00.498 position:10% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] My point is, I think
you're up to something unsavory.

00:14:00.531 --> 00:14:01.866 position:35% line:89% align:start
Inspector,

00:14:01.900 --> 00:14:04.903 position:13% line:83% align:start
we're moving forward with
a number of new projects.

00:14:04.936 --> 00:14:06.704 position:5% line:89% align:start
Whether or not they're "savory"

00:14:06.738 --> 00:14:09.607 position:27% line:83% align:start
depends upon how
you look at them.

00:14:11.509 --> 00:14:13.978 position:30% line:89% align:start
Yes, I'm sure.

00:14:14.012 --> 00:14:16.547 position:27% line:83% align:start
We'll talk after
the interrogation.

00:14:35.600 --> 00:14:36.768 position:41% line:83% align:start
[MIKA]
Chief?

00:14:36.801 --> 00:14:40.939 position:10% line:83% align:start
Inspector Shimotsuki. Please
come to my office, at once.

00:14:46.878 --> 00:14:49.647 position:19% line:89% align:start
[indistinct murmuring]

00:14:51.083 --> 00:14:52.483 position:21% line:89% align:start
He proposed to you?

00:14:52.517 --> 00:14:53.818 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAORI]
Yup.

00:14:53.851 --> 00:14:56.188 position:19% line:89% align:start
However, he's so busy.

00:14:57.289 --> 00:14:58.990 position:13% line:89% align:start
You know how work can be.

00:14:59.023 --> 00:15:01.659 position:19% line:83% align:start
So the actual wedding
won't be for a while.

00:15:02.860 --> 00:15:07.099 position:7% line:83% align:start
You'll love him. I can't wait
for you two to meet in person!

00:15:07.765 --> 00:15:08.800 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh.

00:15:08.833 --> 00:15:09.801 position:27% line:89% align:start
[AKANE chuckles]

00:15:09.834 --> 00:15:12.904 position:19% line:83% align:start
I can't believe one of
us is getting married!

00:15:12.937 --> 00:15:13.905 position:27% line:89% align:start
Congratulations.

00:15:13.938 --> 00:15:15.174 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckles]

00:15:15.207 --> 00:15:16.841 position:30% line:89% align:start
Thanks, Akane.

00:15:18.543 --> 00:15:20.611 position:13% line:83% align:start
[KAORI] We got matched up
through the Sibyl System.

00:15:20.645 --> 00:15:23.748 position:7% line:83% align:start
All this time, I'd held off on
using it, but I have to admit,

00:15:23.781 --> 00:15:27.119 position:7% line:83% align:start
it did a better job of finding
me a partner than I ever have.

00:15:27.152 --> 00:15:31.856 position:13% line:83% align:start
Anyway, it wasn't too long
before we let our parents know.

00:15:31.889 --> 00:15:33.958 position:13% line:89% align:start
It hasn't all been smooth.

00:15:33.992 --> 00:15:37.762 position:13% line:83% align:start
But ups and downs in love,
that's just normal.

00:15:37.795 --> 00:15:39.664 position:21% line:89% align:start
I mean, big picture.

00:15:39.697 --> 00:15:43.168 position:13% line:83% align:start
When Sibyl says it's found
the perfect man for you...

00:15:43.202 --> 00:15:47.005 position:33% line:83% align:start
It's like...
who am I to argue, right?

00:15:47.038 --> 00:15:48.539 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
You'll be fine.

00:15:53.611 --> 00:15:56.781 position:7% line:83% align:start
[KAORI] We really are blessed
to live in such peaceful times.

00:15:56.814 --> 00:16:00.718 position:19% line:83% align:start
And it's all thanks to
where you work. The MWPSB.

00:16:03.755 --> 00:16:05.923 position:10% line:83% align:start
[KAORI] Sibyl not only knows
the path to true happiness

00:16:05.957 --> 00:16:09.328 position:16% line:83% align:start
for every single person
in Japan, she sees that path

00:16:09.361 --> 00:16:12.764 position:10% line:83% align:start
clearer than they could ever
hope to see it themselves.

00:16:12.797 --> 00:16:14.899 position:5% line:89% align:start
I'm starting to think, one day,

00:16:14.932 --> 00:16:19.937 position:13% line:83% align:start
Sibyl might actually save
everyone in the whole world.

00:16:19.971 --> 00:16:21.806 position:27% line:89% align:start
I-I don't know.

00:16:21.839 --> 00:16:23.342 position:10% line:83% align:start
[NEWS ORB] And now, we turn
to the Sibyl System

00:16:23.375 --> 00:16:26.778 position:7% line:83% align:start
exportation program, which is
providing government assistance

00:16:26.811 --> 00:16:27.945 position:35% line:89% align:start
to SEAUn.

00:16:27.979 --> 00:16:29.614 position:24% line:83% align:start
Officials tell us
Sibyl's test run

00:16:29.647 --> 00:16:31.883 position:13% line:83% align:start
in the SEAUn capital city
of Shambhala Float,

00:16:31.916 --> 00:16:33.318 position:24% line:83% align:start
has worked through
its teething problems

00:16:33.352 --> 00:16:36.687 position:10% line:83% align:start
and is now fully operational
and running smoothly.

00:16:36.721 --> 00:16:37.755 position:16% line:89% align:start
And with this success...

00:16:37.789 --> 00:16:39.757 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAORI]
See? Just like I said.

00:16:39.791 --> 00:16:42.994 position:21% line:83% align:start
Now Sibyl's bringing
peace and love to everyone!

00:16:58.177 --> 00:17:01.646 position:27% line:89% align:start
[AKANE grunting]

00:17:01.679 --> 00:17:05.683 position:35% line:89% align:start
[panting]

00:17:07.919 --> 00:17:08.920 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE grunts]

00:17:52.297 --> 00:17:54.099 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Where is he?

00:17:54.133 --> 00:17:56.101 position:21% line:89% align:start
And what's he doing?

00:18:01.306 --> 00:18:05.009 position:35% line:89% align:start
[ringing]

00:18:05.042 --> 00:18:06.111 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE groans]

00:18:06.145 --> 00:18:08.447 position:35% line:89% align:start
[ringing]

00:18:08.480 --> 00:18:11.083 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE grunts]

00:18:12.417 --> 00:18:16.053 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Hey, Shion. What's up?

00:18:16.088 --> 00:18:17.356 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SHION]
Before I start,

00:18:17.389 --> 00:18:20.057 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm calling you on
a concealed channel.

00:18:20.092 --> 00:18:22.361 position:21% line:83% align:start
Don't tell anyone we
had this conversation.

00:18:22.394 --> 00:18:24.096 position:24% line:89% align:start
It never happened.

00:18:24.129 --> 00:18:27.132 position:16% line:83% align:start
Shimotsuki, she's acting
on the Chief's orders.

00:18:27.166 --> 00:18:28.900 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Acting how?

00:18:28.933 --> 00:18:30.369 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SHION]
Point is, in my position,

00:18:30.402 --> 00:18:32.036 position:13% line:89% align:start
I couldn't say no to her.

00:18:32.070 --> 00:18:33.405 position:27% line:83% align:start
You should come
to the office, quick.

00:18:33.438 --> 00:18:34.672 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
I'm coming now.

00:18:34.705 --> 00:18:38.009 position:5% line:83% align:start
Whatever she's asked you to do,
you have to find a way to stall.

00:18:39.077 --> 00:18:40.778 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Well? Can you?!

00:18:40.811 --> 00:18:42.080 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SHION]
I can't.

00:18:42.114 --> 00:18:45.450 position:5% line:89% align:start
It's too late. I'm sorry, Akane.

00:18:48.753 --> 00:18:51.290 position:16% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] You did a memory
scoop for the interrogation?

00:18:51.323 --> 00:18:52.924 position:19% line:89% align:start
Why would you do that?

00:18:52.957 --> 00:18:54.992 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SHION]
Please, don't be mad.

00:18:55.026 --> 00:18:57.028 position:41% line:83% align:start
[MIKA]
It was the Chief's orders.

00:18:57.062 --> 00:19:00.299 position:24% line:83% align:start
Analyst Karanomori
was only doing her job.

00:19:02.800 --> 00:19:05.803 position:13% line:83% align:start
The memory scoop confirmed
he's a latent criminal.

00:19:05.836 --> 00:19:09.208 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's not like it's illegal.
Just unprecedented.

00:19:09.241 --> 00:19:10.908 position:38% line:89% align:start
[sighs]

00:19:20.818 --> 00:19:22.053 position:38% line:89% align:start
Oh, no.

00:19:23.054 --> 00:19:25.056 position:24% line:83% align:start
[MIKA] We did use
some neurological drugs

00:19:25.090 --> 00:19:27.058 position:21% line:83% align:start
in order to improve
brain wave detection.

00:19:27.092 --> 00:19:28.293 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE gasps]

00:19:28.327 --> 00:19:30.795 position:21% line:83% align:start
We're talking about
armed illegal aliens.

00:19:30.828 --> 00:19:32.797 position:19% line:89% align:start
That's a major threat.

00:19:32.830 --> 00:19:34.765 position:13% line:89% align:start
He was a latent criminal.

00:19:34.799 --> 00:19:38.002 position:13% line:83% align:start
Civil rights aren't a big
concern in a case like this one.

00:19:38.035 --> 00:19:40.539 position:5% line:89% align:start
And the procedure was a success.

00:19:40.572 --> 00:19:41.573 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
It was?

00:19:41.607 --> 00:19:44.476 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm glad you came.
The Chief wants to see you.

00:19:45.477 --> 00:19:47.312 position:21% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] Why did you
order Inspector Shimotsuki

00:19:47.346 --> 00:19:48.879 position:24% line:89% align:start
to do that scoop?

00:19:48.913 --> 00:19:50.549 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KASEI]
I'm investigating the case.

00:19:50.582 --> 00:19:52.117 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
That's ridiculous!

00:19:52.150 --> 00:19:56.053 position:13% line:83% align:start
[KASEI] It's necessary...
under the circumstances.

00:19:56.088 --> 00:19:58.090 position:21% line:89% align:start
Here, look at this.

00:20:01.393 --> 00:20:02.527 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:20:05.130 --> 00:20:07.932 position:21% line:83% align:start
[KASEI] You know who
this man is, don't you?

00:20:09.934 --> 00:20:13.372 position:13% line:83% align:start
[KASEI] If memory serves,
he was your first subordinate.

00:20:16.375 --> 00:20:17.376 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:20:18.343 --> 00:20:19.478 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KASEI]
Those foreign terrorists

00:20:19.511 --> 00:20:22.514 position:21% line:83% align:start
you apprehended and
we "interrogated."

00:20:22.547 --> 00:20:25.883 position:13% line:83% align:start
We found memories of them
working closely with this man,

00:20:25.916 --> 00:20:28.553 position:7% line:89% align:start
who went AWOL three years ago.

00:20:28.587 --> 00:20:31.590 position:5% line:89% align:start
Don't you find that interesting?

00:20:31.623 --> 00:20:33.458 position:24% line:83% align:start
I believe that in
the intervening years,

00:20:33.492 --> 00:20:36.395 position:16% line:83% align:start
Shinya Kogami has turned
completely to crime,

00:20:36.428 --> 00:20:38.297 position:24% line:89% align:start
and now terrorism.

00:20:38.330 --> 00:20:42.833 position:5% line:83% align:start
We also found how they were able
to enter Japan. It was SEAUn.

00:20:42.867 --> 00:20:44.969 position:16% line:83% align:start
The illegals we captured
were heavily involved

00:20:45.002 --> 00:20:48.307 position:24% line:83% align:start
in anti-government
terrorism in that region.

00:20:48.340 --> 00:20:51.876 position:13% line:83% align:start
We have high level ties to
the Southeast Asian UN now.

00:20:51.909 --> 00:20:53.412 position:19% line:89% align:start
We're exporting Sibyl.

00:20:53.445 --> 00:20:55.314 position:7% line:89% align:start
That's right. As a test to see

00:20:55.347 --> 00:20:58.550 position:7% line:83% align:start
if Sibyl can remotely monitor
people thousands of miles away,

00:20:58.583 --> 00:21:01.286 position:16% line:83% align:start
they've built a special
administrative district.

00:21:01.320 --> 00:21:02.587 position:5% line:89% align:start
The whole of their capital city,

00:21:02.621 --> 00:21:06.023 position:21% line:83% align:start
the man-made island
of Shambhala Float.

00:21:06.057 --> 00:21:10.095 position:5% line:83% align:start
Of course, the mainland is still
in a state of internal conflict.

00:21:10.128 --> 00:21:12.230 position:24% line:83% align:start
And increasingly,
the Drones responsible

00:21:12.264 --> 00:21:13.864 position:7% line:89% align:start
for defending Shambhala Float

00:21:13.898 --> 00:21:16.867 position:19% line:83% align:start
are coming under fire
and getting shot down.

00:21:19.371 --> 00:21:22.840 position:13% line:83% align:start
[KASEI] This man resembles
Kogami quite a bit, too.

00:21:23.675 --> 00:21:26.311 position:19% line:83% align:start
There are some hunters
who work with such abandon

00:21:26.345 --> 00:21:27.646 position:27% line:83% align:start
there ceases to
be any difference

00:21:27.679 --> 00:21:29.947 position:27% line:83% align:start
between them and
the prey they hunt.

00:21:30.948 --> 00:21:33.652 position:10% line:83% align:start
We don't know how he escaped
Japan three years ago,

00:21:33.685 --> 00:21:35.554 position:27% line:83% align:start
but suppose that
really is Kogami

00:21:35.587 --> 00:21:38.457 position:24% line:83% align:start
hiding out in the
turmoil of the SEAUn.

00:21:38.490 --> 00:21:39.890 position:19% line:89% align:start
And using it as a base

00:21:39.924 --> 00:21:42.661 position:24% line:83% align:start
from which to send
armed terrorists here.

00:21:42.694 --> 00:21:45.263 position:24% line:83% align:start
It's a good way to
attack the Sibyl System.

00:21:45.297 --> 00:21:47.666 position:10% line:89% align:start
Don't you agree, Inspector?

00:21:47.699 --> 00:21:50.935 position:21% line:83% align:start
But Enforcer Kogami
would never do that.

00:21:50.968 --> 00:21:52.002 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KASEI]
Then how do you explain

00:21:52.036 --> 00:21:54.172 position:30% line:83% align:start
this brainwave
composite picture?

00:21:55.173 --> 00:21:58.008 position:19% line:83% align:start
Kogami may've crossed
paths with them.

00:21:58.042 --> 00:22:01.011 position:5% line:83% align:start
Maybe he does have a connection
to the terrorist group.

00:22:01.045 --> 00:22:03.682 position:16% line:83% align:start
But that said, we still
have no definitive proof

00:22:03.715 --> 00:22:06.418 position:5% line:89% align:start
he's become a criminal himself.

00:22:06.451 --> 00:22:09.154 position:21% line:83% align:start
Our next step should
be an investigation

00:22:09.187 --> 00:22:11.021 position:19% line:89% align:start
to uncover the truth.

00:22:17.562 --> 00:22:19.064 position:19% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] It didn't take
long to figure out

00:22:19.097 --> 00:22:21.166 position:5% line:89% align:start
the country you guys came from.

00:22:21.199 --> 00:22:24.136 position:24% line:83% align:start
Why'd you come to
Japan from SEAUn?

00:22:24.169 --> 00:22:26.304 position:10% line:83% align:start
Does it have something to do
with the Japanese government

00:22:26.338 --> 00:22:28.407 position:21% line:83% align:start
exporting the Sibyl
System to you?

00:22:31.743 --> 00:22:33.478 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
If you won't answer that,

00:22:33.512 --> 00:22:36.248 position:24% line:83% align:start
maybe you can tell
me about this man.

00:22:36.281 --> 00:22:40.152 position:13% line:83% align:start
And if you refuse to talk
to me, someone else will.

00:22:44.222 --> 00:22:47.292 position:10% line:83% align:start
Ask whoever you want, lady.
No one's talking to you.

00:22:47.325 --> 00:22:48.427 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Is that so?

00:22:48.460 --> 00:22:52.297 position:16% line:83% align:start
You're the insane ones.
You lost sight of true justice

00:22:52.330 --> 00:22:55.534 position:16% line:83% align:start
when you handed over our
fates to a computer oracle.

00:22:57.235 --> 00:23:00.572 position:5% line:83% align:start
[MA] Whatever you get out of us
won't make sense to you, anyway.

00:23:02.441 --> 00:23:03.575 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE grunts]

00:23:11.349 --> 00:23:13.552 position:10% line:83% align:start
[SAIGA] Would Shinya Kogami
provide his talents

00:23:13.585 --> 00:23:15.654 position:13% line:89% align:start
to a group of terrorists?

00:23:15.687 --> 00:23:18.123 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Yes. Not leading them, though.

00:23:18.156 --> 00:23:20.358 position:24% line:83% align:start
More like, serving
as a consultant.

00:23:20.392 --> 00:23:21.560 position:13% line:89% align:start
Helping to organize them,

00:23:21.593 --> 00:23:24.529 position:27% line:83% align:start
offering advice
on their strategy.

00:23:24.563 --> 00:23:27.699 position:7% line:83% align:start
Do you think Kogami is capable
of being something like that?

00:23:28.533 --> 00:23:32.270 position:16% line:83% align:start
[SAIGA] So... basically
a kind of inspiration,

00:23:32.304 --> 00:23:34.339 position:19% line:89% align:start
like Shogo Makishima.

00:23:34.372 --> 00:23:35.407 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Yes.

00:23:35.440 --> 00:23:38.176 position:19% line:83% align:start
[SAIGA] I really want
to say that's impossible.

00:23:38.210 --> 00:23:40.178 position:10% line:89% align:start
But I think my fond memories

00:23:40.212 --> 00:23:42.647 position:24% line:83% align:start
for Kogami may be
clouding that judgment.

00:23:44.483 --> 00:23:46.418 position:13% line:83% align:start
[SAIGA] Given what you've
said of his recent actions,

00:23:46.451 --> 00:23:49.421 position:21% line:83% align:start
I can't predict his
behavior anymore.

00:23:49.454 --> 00:23:50.589 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
But...

00:23:50.622 --> 00:23:53.158 position:13% line:83% align:start
[SAIGA] Some people try to
find meaning in their lives

00:23:53.191 --> 00:23:55.193 position:19% line:83% align:start
by fitting themselves
into a mold,

00:23:55.227 --> 00:23:57.462 position:27% line:83% align:start
or role they can
play in society.

00:23:57.496 --> 00:23:59.164 position:5% line:89% align:start
And, in turn, that's why you see

00:23:59.197 --> 00:24:01.600 position:21% line:83% align:start
so many devote their
lives to their work.

00:24:03.235 --> 00:24:06.438 position:5% line:83% align:start
[SAIGA] Kogami used to live this
way when he was an Enforcer.

00:24:08.373 --> 00:24:10.408 position:24% line:83% align:start
But, while chasing
after a target

00:24:10.442 --> 00:24:14.279 position:10% line:83% align:start
who didn't fit into society
at all, that being Makishima,

00:24:14.312 --> 00:24:17.749 position:21% line:83% align:start
he, too, ultimately
broke free from a mold.

00:24:17.782 --> 00:24:20.352 position:10% line:89% align:start
The mold that was his duty.

00:24:25.524 --> 00:24:29.394 position:10% line:83% align:start
[KASEI] Hm? You're applying
for an investigation abroad?

00:24:29.427 --> 00:24:30.629 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Yes.

00:24:30.662 --> 00:24:33.832 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KASEI]
You're going to SEAUn yourself?

00:24:33.865 --> 00:24:36.368 position:13% line:83% align:start
Security in the Shambhala
Float special district

00:24:36.401 --> 00:24:38.270 position:10% line:89% align:start
is run by the Sibyl System.

00:24:38.303 --> 00:24:40.272 position:27% line:83% align:start
That is to say,
police authority there

00:24:40.305 --> 00:24:43.074 position:13% line:83% align:start
lies with the Ministry of
Welfare here in Japan.

00:24:43.108 --> 00:24:46.244 position:21% line:83% align:start
So. You'll find your
actions legally protected

00:24:46.278 --> 00:24:48.246 position:27% line:83% align:start
by right of the
Public Safety Bureau.

00:24:48.280 --> 00:24:50.582 position:7% line:89% align:start
A subsidiary of the Ministry.

00:24:50.615 --> 00:24:51.850 position:35% line:89% align:start
One catch.

00:24:51.883 --> 00:24:55.620 position:7% line:83% align:start
Outside the special district,
your privileges won't matter.

00:24:55.654 --> 00:24:58.156 position:13% line:83% align:start
Because outside the walls
of Shambhala Float,

00:24:58.189 --> 00:25:00.592 position:21% line:89% align:start
they respect no law.

00:25:00.625 --> 00:25:02.260 position:10% line:89% align:start
Your investigation of Kogami

00:25:02.294 --> 00:25:05.363 position:24% line:83% align:start
will have to be an
independent endeavor.

00:25:05.397 --> 00:25:07.599 position:24% line:89% align:start
Do you understand?

00:25:07.632 --> 00:25:09.234 position:27% line:89% align:start
I know the risk.

00:25:10.368 --> 00:25:11.836 position:16% line:83% align:start
[KASEI] We have a flight
leaving for SEAUn

00:25:11.870 --> 00:25:14.306 position:16% line:89% align:start
early tomorrow morning.

00:25:14.339 --> 00:25:17.342 position:7% line:83% align:start
It's a transport jet carrying
precision equipment.

00:25:17.375 --> 00:25:20.512 position:30% line:83% align:start
So... How many
guards would you like?

00:25:21.613 --> 00:25:23.348 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
I'm fine by myself.

00:25:23.381 --> 00:25:24.449 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KASEI]
To be frank,

00:25:24.482 --> 00:25:27.185 position:10% line:83% align:start
considering the relationship
between you and "us,"

00:25:27.218 --> 00:25:29.554 position:7% line:89% align:start
your traveling alone is ideal.

00:25:34.759 --> 00:25:35.860 position:38% line:83% align:start
[GINOZA]
For the record,

00:25:35.894 --> 00:25:38.863 position:19% line:83% align:start
they denied my request
to go with you.

00:25:38.897 --> 00:25:40.632 position:21% line:89% align:start
That's no surprise.

00:25:40.665 --> 00:25:44.569 position:7% line:83% align:start
Sending an Inspector overseas
is already unusual enough.

00:25:44.603 --> 00:25:47.238 position:21% line:83% align:start
An Enforcer's where
they draw the line.

00:25:48.340 --> 00:25:49.808 position:38% line:83% align:start
[GINOZA]
I need a favor.

00:25:49.841 --> 00:25:51.443 position:33% line:89% align:start
Yeah, sure.

00:25:51.476 --> 00:25:53.378 position:19% line:89% align:start
If you do find Shinya.

00:25:53.411 --> 00:25:57.148 position:19% line:83% align:start
Go right up to him and
punch him in the face for me.

00:25:59.417 --> 00:26:01.319 position:19% line:89% align:start
I'm not gonna hit him.

00:26:01.353 --> 00:26:03.154 position:35% line:89% align:start
Why? Uh...

00:26:05.757 --> 00:26:10.195 position:7% line:83% align:start
If I find him, I'll arrest him
and bring him back to you.

00:26:10.228 --> 00:26:11.162 position:13% line:89% align:start
Then you can have the fun

00:26:11.196 --> 00:26:13.632 position:21% line:83% align:start
of working him over
yourself, Mister Ginoza.

00:26:14.833 --> 00:26:16.468 position:24% line:89% align:start
[GINOZA chuckles]

00:26:16.501 --> 00:26:18.703 position:27% line:83% align:start
I can't tell if
you've really changed,

00:26:18.737 --> 00:26:21.573 position:19% line:83% align:start
or if you're the same
person you always were.

00:26:21.606 --> 00:26:24.442 position:24% line:83% align:start
A mystery wearing
an Inspector's jacket.

00:26:36.855 --> 00:26:39.424 position:10% line:83% align:start
[CREW] You're the lady from
the Ministry of Welfare, right?

00:26:39.457 --> 00:26:40.625 position:27% line:89% align:start
Welcome aboard.

00:26:40.659 --> 00:26:43.361 position:24% line:83% align:start
Thanks for taking
me on last minute.

00:26:43.395 --> 00:26:45.830 position:7% line:83% align:start
It's been a while since we've
moved cargo with a pulse,

00:26:45.864 --> 00:26:47.766 position:19% line:89% align:start
let alone a cute girl.

00:27:13.425 --> 00:27:15.660 position:13% line:83% align:start
[SAIGA] Despite countless
cultures' best efforts,

00:27:15.694 --> 00:27:18.296 position:7% line:83% align:start
many different order and value
systems have disappeared

00:27:18.329 --> 00:27:20.432 position:7% line:89% align:start
into chaos over the millennia.

00:27:20.465 --> 00:27:21.933 position:24% line:83% align:start
The common thread
in those failures

00:27:21.966 --> 00:27:25.470 position:10% line:83% align:start
being that most people feel
compelled to live like animals,

00:27:25.503 --> 00:27:28.306 position:19% line:83% align:start
allowing themselves to
be ruled by their desires.

00:27:28.339 --> 00:27:29.941 position:24% line:83% align:start
Your choice is to
be either tamed

00:27:29.974 --> 00:27:32.343 position:5% line:89% align:start
within the Sibyl System's cage,

00:27:32.377 --> 00:27:34.779 position:19% line:83% align:start
or to live in a state
of nature and be free

00:27:34.813 --> 00:27:38.650 position:10% line:83% align:start
by committing yourself only
to the laws of the jungle.

00:27:38.683 --> 00:27:39.884 position:24% line:89% align:start
Neither is ideal.

00:27:39.918 --> 00:27:43.288 position:7% line:83% align:start
A place where man can maintain
his ideology and his dignity

00:27:43.321 --> 00:27:45.523 position:7% line:89% align:start
no longer exists in our world.

00:27:46.925 --> 00:27:49.761 position:16% line:83% align:start
In this setting, letting
instinct and willpower

00:27:49.794 --> 00:27:53.364 position:10% line:83% align:start
alone be your guide, to take
control of your own fate

00:27:53.398 --> 00:27:55.467 position:21% line:83% align:start
and live under your
own value system

00:27:55.500 --> 00:27:58.837 position:16% line:83% align:start
must seem like the most
intoxicating of lures.

00:27:58.870 --> 00:28:01.906 position:13% line:83% align:start
Especially to those who're
driven into such a corner

00:28:01.940 --> 00:28:02.874 position:5% line:89% align:start
that they've even become willing

00:28:02.907 --> 00:28:06.444 position:21% line:83% align:start
to commit crimes and
acts of terror. Right?

00:28:07.846 --> 00:28:08.947 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SAIGA]
That is the paradigm

00:28:08.980 --> 00:28:12.717 position:21% line:83% align:start
our old antagonist,
Shogo Makishima, experienced.

00:28:12.751 --> 00:28:16.521 position:5% line:83% align:start
And something that Kogami showed
us when he finally caught up

00:28:16.554 --> 00:28:20.759 position:16% line:83% align:start
to his prey in the field
that day, and killed him.

00:28:20.792 --> 00:28:22.260 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Yeah.

00:28:29.601 --> 00:28:32.737 position:7% line:89% align:start
So. Do they know your secret?

00:28:32.771 --> 00:28:35.740 position:30% line:83% align:start
Does the SEAUn
know your true form?

00:28:35.774 --> 00:28:37.542 position:16% line:83% align:start
--[KASEI] Of course not.
--[AKANE gasps]

00:28:38.543 --> 00:28:40.912 position:16% line:83% align:start
How could we reveal such
a secret to foreign countries

00:28:40.945 --> 00:28:43.314 position:24% line:83% align:start
when we can't even
do it in our own?

00:28:43.348 --> 00:28:46.551 position:10% line:83% align:start
Right now, we've only given
two technologies to the SEAUn.

00:28:46.584 --> 00:28:48.753 position:13% line:83% align:start
Street equipment for them
to measure cymatic scans

00:28:48.787 --> 00:28:51.090 position:24% line:83% align:start
in the people, and
special network bandwidth

00:28:51.123 --> 00:28:54.726 position:19% line:83% align:start
for that scan data to
be sent back to Japan.

00:28:54.759 --> 00:28:55.994 position:7% line:89% align:start
We're not sending Dominators,

00:28:56.027 --> 00:28:57.862 position:21% line:83% align:start
nor are they allowed
to use them,

00:28:57.896 --> 00:29:00.398 position:27% line:83% align:start
and security is
maintained not by us,

00:29:00.431 --> 00:29:03.434 position:19% line:83% align:start
but by their own Union
Military Police force.

00:29:03.468 --> 00:29:04.402 position:21% line:89% align:start
As far as they know,

00:29:04.435 --> 00:29:07.438 position:21% line:83% align:start
the Sibyl System is
nothing but a black box.

00:29:07.472 --> 00:29:10.475 position:21% line:83% align:start
In a basement server
room across the ocean.

00:29:12.811 --> 00:29:14.946 position:7% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] I'm surprised Chairman
Hang accepted a system

00:29:14.979 --> 00:29:15.914 position:13% line:89% align:start
where the main requirement

00:29:15.947 --> 00:29:19.050 position:21% line:83% align:start
is he be kept in the
dark on most details.

00:29:19.084 --> 00:29:20.852 position:19% line:83% align:start
[KASEI] It just shows
how desperate they are

00:29:20.885 --> 00:29:24.656 position:16% line:83% align:start
to restore public safety
as quickly as possible.

00:29:24.689 --> 00:29:26.658 position:16% line:89% align:start
This'll be good for you.

00:29:26.691 --> 00:29:28.426 position:16% line:83% align:start
You'll see for yourself
how hard it is

00:29:28.459 --> 00:29:32.064 position:10% line:83% align:start
for countries outside Japan
to maintain internal peace.

00:29:32.097 --> 00:29:34.866 position:24% line:83% align:start
And with that view
will come understanding

00:29:34.899 --> 00:29:36.901 position:10% line:89% align:start
of the great value to be had

00:29:36.935 --> 00:29:40.471 position:19% line:83% align:start
in controlling society
with the Sibyl System.

00:29:52.584 --> 00:29:54.119 position:41% line:89% align:start
[ding]

00:29:54.153 --> 00:29:56.988 position:7% line:83% align:start
[PILOT] We should have you on
the ground in about 15 minutes.

00:29:57.021 --> 00:29:59.657 position:10% line:83% align:start
Please fasten your seatbelts
as we begin our final approach

00:29:59.691 --> 00:30:01.993 position:35% line:83% align:start
into SEAUn
International Airport.

00:30:29.621 --> 00:30:31.190 position:13% line:89% align:start
I'm Nicholas Wong, ma'am.

00:30:31.223 --> 00:30:33.958 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'm Captain of the Union
Military Police force.

00:30:33.992 --> 00:30:36.895 position:16% line:83% align:start
And I assume you must be
Inspector Akane Tsunemori

00:30:36.928 --> 00:30:39.198 position:13% line:83% align:start
from the Japanese Ministry
of Health and Welfare.

00:30:39.231 --> 00:30:40.431 position:41% line:89% align:start
I am.

00:30:43.168 --> 00:30:46.704 position:21% line:83% align:start
Then welcome to the
Southeast Asian UN.

00:30:46.738 --> 00:30:49.407 position:21% line:83% align:start
We're happy to have
both you and Sibyl.

00:30:51.210 --> 00:30:54.012 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
Does our country shock you?

00:30:54.045 --> 00:30:55.214 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
No.

00:30:55.247 --> 00:30:58.716 position:10% line:83% align:start
From what I hear, it's like
this now in every country.

00:30:58.750 --> 00:31:00.152 position:30% line:89% align:start
Except Japan.

00:31:11.930 --> 00:31:15.667 position:21% line:83% align:start
What about the area
we're in now? Is it unsafe?

00:31:15.700 --> 00:31:17.902 position:10% line:83% align:start
Well, it's certainly better
than it used to be.

00:31:17.936 --> 00:31:21.572 position:10% line:83% align:start
We've been able to eliminate
all the major military factions.

00:31:21.606 --> 00:31:24.609 position:21% line:83% align:start
We believe the civil
war is nearing an end.

00:31:24.642 --> 00:31:26.477 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
From how you word that,

00:31:26.511 --> 00:31:29.013 position:24% line:83% align:start
it sounds like the
war's still going.

00:31:29.047 --> 00:31:30.915 position:13% line:89% align:start
And you would be correct.

00:31:31.883 --> 00:31:33.085 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
There are still some dissidents

00:31:33.118 --> 00:31:34.719 position:33% line:83% align:start
waging their
delusional rebellion

00:31:34.752 --> 00:31:37.055 position:27% line:83% align:start
against Chairman
Hang's government.

00:31:46.198 --> 00:31:48.566 position:10% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS] Just ahead is the
Shambhala Special District,

00:31:48.599 --> 00:31:50.969 position:19% line:83% align:start
where Sibyl's running
on a trial basis.

00:31:52.036 --> 00:31:54.139 position:13% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS] Only those with
Hues and Crime Coefficients

00:31:54.173 --> 00:31:57.809 position:7% line:83% align:start
certified "normal" are allowed
to enter the District.

00:31:57.842 --> 00:32:00.044 position:35% line:89% align:start
[knocking]

00:32:00.079 --> 00:32:01.579 position:19% line:83% align:start
[MOTHER] Please, sir,
let us enter...

00:32:01.612 --> 00:32:03.815 position:21% line:83% align:start
And we owe it all to
your country's help.

00:32:03.848 --> 00:32:05.184 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTHER]
Please! I have a baby!

00:32:05.217 --> 00:32:06.218 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
Keep driving.

00:32:06.251 --> 00:32:08.987 position:24% line:83% align:start
[MOTHER] Help us!
We can't last long out here!

00:32:09.020 --> 00:32:09.821 position:30% line:89% align:start
No, let us in!

00:32:09.854 --> 00:32:11.156 position:21% line:83% align:start
--[SOLDIER A grunts]
--[MOTHER yelps]

00:32:12.056 --> 00:32:13.658 position:33% line:83% align:start
[SOLDIER B]
Move and we shoot!

00:32:13.691 --> 00:32:15.893 position:10% line:83% align:start
--[SOLDIERS] Get back! Hey!
--[CROWD chatters]

00:32:15.927 --> 00:32:17.562 position:35% line:89% align:start
[gunfire]

00:32:19.131 --> 00:32:21.066 position:21% line:83% align:start
Don't let it bother
you, Inspector.

00:32:21.100 --> 00:32:23.102 position:13% line:89% align:start
This happens all the time.

00:33:03.875 --> 00:33:04.976 position:33% line:83% align:start
[ANNOUNCER]
This bus is reserved

00:33:05.009 --> 00:33:08.247 position:19% line:83% align:start
for residents who are
authorized by the Sibyl System.

00:33:12.184 --> 00:33:14.219 position:19% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] Who are those
people wearing collars?

00:33:14.253 --> 00:33:18.190 position:10% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS] Those sad-looking
souls are latent criminals.

00:33:18.223 --> 00:33:19.091 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:33:19.124 --> 00:33:19.791 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
Rather than locking them up,

00:33:19.824 --> 00:33:21.959 position:5% line:89% align:start
we give them freedom of movement

00:33:21.993 --> 00:33:25.696 position:13% line:83% align:start
and that device to monitor
their Psycho-Passes.

00:33:25.730 --> 00:33:26.764 position:21% line:89% align:start
If their Hue clouds,

00:33:26.798 --> 00:33:29.600 position:16% line:83% align:start
we'll instantly measure
their Crime Coefficients.

00:33:29.634 --> 00:33:30.802 position:13% line:89% align:start
Depending on that number,

00:33:30.835 --> 00:33:34.772 position:10% line:83% align:start
the collars will then inject
either anesthesia or poison.

00:33:36.741 --> 00:33:38.810 position:7% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS] We can't have those
with high Crime Coefficients

00:33:38.843 --> 00:33:40.044 position:5% line:89% align:start
living among the general public,

00:33:40.079 --> 00:33:44.083 position:7% line:83% align:start
what with the impact that can
have on Area Stress Levels.

00:33:44.116 --> 00:33:45.750 position:21% line:83% align:start
Of course, since we
haven't been able to build

00:33:45.783 --> 00:33:48.619 position:16% line:83% align:start
big isolation facilities
like you have in Japan,

00:33:48.653 --> 00:33:50.755 position:33% line:83% align:start
this is only
a temporary measure.

00:33:51.856 --> 00:33:54.093 position:27% line:83% align:start
I see that some
of them are soldiers.

00:33:54.126 --> 00:33:55.094 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
Yes,

00:33:55.127 --> 00:33:57.628 position:19% line:83% align:start
in a sense, they fill
the role of Enforcers.

00:33:57.662 --> 00:33:59.364 position:21% line:83% align:start
But their orders all
come from officers

00:33:59.398 --> 00:34:01.666 position:7% line:89% align:start
who must maintain a clear Hue.

00:34:01.699 --> 00:34:04.169 position:21% line:83% align:start
Officers are kind of
like our Inspectors.

00:34:04.203 --> 00:34:06.838 position:13% line:83% align:start
One more piece of advice,
Ms. Tsunemori.

00:34:06.871 --> 00:34:07.705 position:33% line:89% align:start
What is it?

00:34:07.738 --> 00:34:08.906 position:24% line:89% align:start
During your stay,

00:34:08.940 --> 00:34:10.975 position:27% line:83% align:start
if you leave the
Shambhala Special District,

00:34:11.008 --> 00:34:13.278 position:21% line:83% align:start
or go out to inspect
a government facility,

00:34:13.312 --> 00:34:15.247 position:19% line:83% align:start
please make sure that
you have one of our guards

00:34:15.280 --> 00:34:18.350 position:16% line:83% align:start
accompanying you at all
times for your protection.

00:34:18.383 --> 00:34:20.818 position:19% line:89% align:start
At all times? Really?

00:34:20.852 --> 00:34:22.421 position:24% line:89% align:start
Is that a problem?

00:34:22.454 --> 00:34:23.654 position:44% line:89% align:start
No.

00:34:37.269 --> 00:34:38.870 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
I'm Akane Tsunemori,

00:34:38.903 --> 00:34:41.739 position:13% line:83% align:start
Inspector for the Japanese
Ministry of Welfare,

00:34:41.772 --> 00:34:43.308 position:16% line:89% align:start
Public Safety Division.

00:34:43.342 --> 00:34:45.144 position:41% line:83% align:start
[HANG]
And I'm Chuang Hang.

00:34:46.111 --> 00:34:47.279 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
It's an honor.

00:34:47.312 --> 00:34:49.448 position:13% line:83% align:start
I never expected that the
chairman of the SEAUn himself

00:34:49.481 --> 00:34:50.582 position:10% line:89% align:start
would want to meet with me.

00:34:50.616 --> 00:34:52.950 position:7% line:83% align:start
[HANG] Take it as a compliment
of how interested we are

00:34:52.984 --> 00:34:55.420 position:16% line:83% align:start
in you and your country,
Miss Tsunemori.

00:34:55.454 --> 00:34:57.788 position:19% line:83% align:start
You must be tired from
your long journey.

00:34:57.822 --> 00:34:59.458 position:5% line:89% align:start
Please, take a seat right here.

00:34:59.491 --> 00:35:00.791 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Thank you.

00:35:03.395 --> 00:35:05.464 position:21% line:83% align:start
We're conducting an
international investigation

00:35:05.497 --> 00:35:07.399 position:10% line:89% align:start
and I'm hoping you can help.

00:35:07.432 --> 00:35:09.767 position:24% line:83% align:start
Yes, by all means,
I'll do what I can.

00:35:09.800 --> 00:35:10.701 position:21% line:89% align:start
The man you're after

00:35:10.735 --> 00:35:13.205 position:19% line:83% align:start
is a terrorist working
for the guerillas?

00:35:13.238 --> 00:35:15.407 position:19% line:83% align:start
Yes, that's the crime
we suspect him of.

00:35:15.440 --> 00:35:18.943 position:10% line:83% align:start
Well. Around here our method
of dealing with guerillas

00:35:18.976 --> 00:35:23.047 position:7% line:83% align:start
is to actively suppress them.
We don't simply "investigate."

00:35:24.116 --> 00:35:26.385 position:19% line:83% align:start
Of course, as I said,
we're happy to help.

00:35:26.418 --> 00:35:28.953 position:13% line:83% align:start
I just wanted to be clear
that conditions in this country

00:35:28.986 --> 00:35:31.390 position:16% line:83% align:start
are different from what
you find in Japan.

00:35:31.423 --> 00:35:34.825 position:16% line:83% align:start
Do try to remember this
during your time here.

00:35:34.859 --> 00:35:36.461 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Of course, sir.

00:35:36.495 --> 00:35:37.429 position:33% line:89% align:start
That's good.

00:35:37.462 --> 00:35:40.265 position:21% line:83% align:start
Colonel Wong, see to
our guest's every need.

00:35:40.299 --> 00:35:42.401 position:7% line:89% align:start
Make sure she's taken care of.

00:35:42.434 --> 00:35:44.436 position:13% line:89% align:start
Yes sir, Mister Chairman.

00:35:49.408 --> 00:35:50.775 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Open case.

00:35:54.346 --> 00:35:55.347 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh.

00:35:58.916 --> 00:36:00.185 position:27% line:89% align:start
[AKANE chuckles]

00:36:00.219 --> 00:36:02.019 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
That's Shion, all right.

00:36:04.789 --> 00:36:05.990 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE sighs]

00:36:07.159 --> 00:36:09.827 position:24% line:89% align:start
[breathes deeply]

00:36:13.465 --> 00:36:16.535 position:21% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] Chuang Hang,
former army general.

00:36:16.568 --> 00:36:18.303 position:30% line:83% align:start
One of several
high-ranking officers

00:36:18.337 --> 00:36:21.340 position:16% line:83% align:start
who led factions during
12 years of civil war,

00:36:21.373 --> 00:36:24.209 position:21% line:83% align:start
fighting each other
for SEAUn control.

00:36:24.243 --> 00:36:27.379 position:13% line:83% align:start
Hang gained the upper hand
by securing support from Japan.

00:36:27.412 --> 00:36:30.449 position:10% line:83% align:start
And to do that, he promised
to establish a special district

00:36:30.482 --> 00:36:32.451 position:24% line:83% align:start
to be governed by
the Sibyl System.

00:36:32.484 --> 00:36:34.986 position:30% line:83% align:start
Two years ago,
he created the new assembly

00:36:35.019 --> 00:36:37.489 position:16% line:83% align:start
and promptly got himself
elected its chairman.

00:36:37.522 --> 00:36:38.590 position:10% line:89% align:start
But, not everyone was happy

00:36:38.624 --> 00:36:41.360 position:16% line:83% align:start
with a military faction
forming the new government.

00:36:41.393 --> 00:36:43.061 position:21% line:83% align:start
These guerillas have
continued to fight

00:36:43.095 --> 00:36:45.796 position:21% line:83% align:start
and make the country
unstable to this day.

00:36:46.931 --> 00:36:48.866 position:10% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] The terrorist group
that came to Japan

00:36:48.899 --> 00:36:52.371 position:13% line:83% align:start
likely belonged to a group
of these anti-Hang guerillas.

00:36:53.938 --> 00:36:55.307 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
It's obvious his grip on power

00:36:55.340 --> 00:36:58.976 position:16% line:83% align:start
is only as strong as the
Japanese government's support.

00:37:00.312 --> 00:37:01.280 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
So is that why

00:37:01.313 --> 00:37:04.349 position:19% line:83% align:start
Tokyo became a terror
target for the rebels?

00:37:06.917 --> 00:37:08.587 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chiming]

00:37:08.620 --> 00:37:09.688 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh.

00:37:11.856 --> 00:37:14.992 position:19% line:83% align:start
Hello, my name is Yeo,
I'll be your personal assistant.

00:37:15.026 --> 00:37:17.229 position:7% line:83% align:start
If there's anything you need,
I've been sent here

00:37:17.262 --> 00:37:20.532 position:13% line:83% align:start
to serve you and only you,
so don't hesitate to ask, okay!

00:37:20.565 --> 00:37:22.301 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckles]

00:37:22.334 --> 00:37:23.302 position:41% line:83% align:start
[YEO]
Are you hungry?

00:37:23.335 --> 00:37:25.504 position:13% line:83% align:start
Breakfast? Lunch? Dinner?
Whatever you like.

00:37:25.537 --> 00:37:27.172 position:19% line:83% align:start
Oh, and they wanted me
to remind you again

00:37:27.205 --> 00:37:29.006 position:21% line:83% align:start
that if you plan on
leaving your room,

00:37:29.040 --> 00:37:32.043 position:24% line:83% align:start
you're free to go
wherever you like in SEAUn.

00:37:32.077 --> 00:37:33.878 position:21% line:83% align:start
So long as you don't
go unaccompanied

00:37:33.911 --> 00:37:37.848 position:13% line:83% align:start
to any major facilities or
the area beyond the bridge.

00:37:37.882 --> 00:37:39.318 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
That won't be a problem.

00:37:40.285 --> 00:37:41.253 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckles]

00:37:41.286 --> 00:37:44.021 position:19% line:83% align:start
[YEO] Oh, and arguably
the most important item:

00:37:44.055 --> 00:37:45.457 position:13% line:83% align:start
In a week, the government
will put a hold

00:37:45.490 --> 00:37:47.526 position:19% line:83% align:start
on all citizens buying
and selling alcohol.

00:37:47.559 --> 00:37:49.494 position:19% line:83% align:start
So if you'd like some,
now would be time.

00:37:49.528 --> 00:37:50.395 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Uh...

00:37:50.429 --> 00:37:52.064 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes?

00:37:52.097 --> 00:37:55.334 position:16% line:83% align:start
Would you be offended if
I asked you a personal question?

00:37:55.367 --> 00:37:57.968 position:10% line:83% align:start
[YEO] Of course not. I just
hope I'm able to answer it.

00:37:58.002 --> 00:38:01.872 position:5% line:83% align:start
Do you have a happy life living
in the Shambhala district?

00:38:01.906 --> 00:38:04.476 position:19% line:89% align:start
Uh... Why, of course!

00:38:04.509 --> 00:38:06.511 position:27% line:83% align:start
Every person in
the special district

00:38:06.545 --> 00:38:09.481 position:7% line:83% align:start
appreciates having a safe life
thanks to Chairman Hang.

00:38:09.514 --> 00:38:12.250 position:16% line:83% align:start
It's because of him that
we have the Sibyl System.

00:38:13.652 --> 00:38:17.289 position:10% line:83% align:start
It wasn't that long ago that
there wasn't a single safe place

00:38:17.322 --> 00:38:19.890 position:10% line:89% align:start
to live in the entire SEAUn!

00:38:47.319 --> 00:38:52.324 position:19% line:89% align:start
[indistinct murmuring]

00:39:12.042 --> 00:39:13.378 position:21% line:89% align:start
[trashcans rattling]

00:39:13.412 --> 00:39:16.081 position:7% line:83% align:start
[CROWD] Hey, what's going on?
Are they going to fight?

00:39:17.082 --> 00:39:17.783 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Uh.

00:39:17.816 --> 00:39:18.717 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SOLDIER]
What's going on--?

00:39:18.750 --> 00:39:20.118 position:19% line:83% align:start
[WAITER] Don't be mad
at me. He did it!

00:39:20.152 --> 00:39:22.254 position:10% line:89% align:start
It's not my fault, I swear!

00:39:24.122 --> 00:39:26.091 position:35% line:89% align:start
[grunting]

00:39:56.221 --> 00:39:57.422 position:33% line:83% align:start
[OPERATOR A]
Parvati Drone.

00:39:57.456 --> 00:39:59.090 position:21% line:89% align:start
Coming up all green.

00:40:00.091 --> 00:40:01.393 position:27% line:89% align:start
Let's move out.

00:40:08.233 --> 00:40:09.501 position:38% line:89% align:start
Damn it.

00:40:15.106 --> 00:40:18.443 position:10% line:83% align:start
If you don't mind, I'd like
to ride along on patrol.

00:40:18.477 --> 00:40:21.213 position:16% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS] By all means,
make yourself comfortable.

00:40:21.246 --> 00:40:23.114 position:7% line:89% align:start
But if we encounter hostility,

00:40:23.148 --> 00:40:26.318 position:21% line:83% align:start
stay out of the way
and don't touch anything.

00:40:26.351 --> 00:40:28.986 position:35% line:83% align:start
Of course.
You won't know I'm here.

00:40:34.092 --> 00:40:37.062 position:21% line:83% align:start
So, can you tell me
where this convoy's headed?

00:40:37.095 --> 00:40:39.331 position:5% line:89% align:start
Fifty kilometers north of here,

00:40:39.364 --> 00:40:42.234 position:16% line:83% align:start
to the ruins of the old
SEAUn capitol city.

00:40:42.267 --> 00:40:44.236 position:19% line:83% align:start
It's normally a ghost
town, but yesterday

00:40:44.269 --> 00:40:47.172 position:13% line:83% align:start
our advance team delivered
a promising bit of intel.

00:40:47.205 --> 00:40:49.207 position:10% line:83% align:start
The guerrillas have moved in
and made it their new base

00:40:49.241 --> 00:40:50.408 position:30% line:83% align:start
for launching
anti-government attacks.

00:40:50.442 --> 00:40:51.743 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SOLDIER]
Back! Get back!

00:40:51.776 --> 00:40:54.112 position:10% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] You guys are leasing
Japanese security Drones

00:40:54.145 --> 00:40:56.481 position:19% line:83% align:start
specifically to patrol
Shambhala, right?

00:40:56.515 --> 00:40:57.582 position:10% line:89% align:start
So why change their mission

00:40:57.616 --> 00:41:00.552 position:21% line:83% align:start
and put them on the
anti-guerrilla beat so far away?

00:41:00.585 --> 00:41:02.420 position:19% line:83% align:start
Hasn't hunting latent
criminals taught you

00:41:02.454 --> 00:41:05.457 position:19% line:83% align:start
that the best defense
is a good offense?

00:41:05.490 --> 00:41:08.627 position:16% line:83% align:start
This doesn't violate the
spirit of our agreement.

00:41:20.505 --> 00:41:22.440 position:16% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS] In our quest
to transform our country

00:41:22.474 --> 00:41:26.511 position:5% line:83% align:start
into a modern society, Shambhala
Float is only the beginning.

00:41:27.546 --> 00:41:30.115 position:5% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS] Eventually, the Sibyl
System's management will extend

00:41:30.148 --> 00:41:33.251 position:24% line:83% align:start
to every corner of
the Southeast Asian UN.

00:41:33.285 --> 00:41:35.453 position:19% line:83% align:start
But we'll only succeed
if we're able to extinguish

00:41:35.487 --> 00:41:37.622 position:16% line:83% align:start
the guerrilla movements
as quickly as possible,

00:41:37.656 --> 00:41:40.725 position:21% line:83% align:start
and then measure the
Psycho-Passes of every citizen.

00:42:21.366 --> 00:42:22.701 position:19% line:89% align:start
Fire when ready, men.

00:42:22.734 --> 00:42:23.802 position:27% line:89% align:start
Roger that, sir.

00:42:23.835 --> 00:42:26.805 position:10% line:83% align:start
All vehicles in the convoy,
switch to battle mode.

00:42:26.838 --> 00:42:28.239 position:19% line:89% align:start
You're "go" to attack.

00:42:29.341 --> 00:42:30.342 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE grunts]

00:42:45.523 --> 00:42:47.859 position:33% line:83% align:start
[GUERRILLA]
Go! Go! Move!

00:42:53.832 --> 00:42:54.833 position:24% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLA yelps]

00:42:56.334 --> 00:42:57.335 position:24% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLA yelps]

00:42:58.503 --> 00:42:59.671 position:24% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLA yelps]

00:42:59.704 --> 00:43:01.172 position:21% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLA panting]

00:43:01.206 --> 00:43:02.207 position:24% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLA yelps]

00:43:10.782 --> 00:43:12.283 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
That's awful.

00:43:12.317 --> 00:43:14.519 position:13% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS] If the cymatic
scan shows no threat,

00:43:14.552 --> 00:43:16.921 position:24% line:83% align:start
the safety on the
cannons will come on.

00:43:19.290 --> 00:43:21.726 position:5% line:83% align:start
Of course, the cannon fire must
mean their crime coefficients

00:43:21.760 --> 00:43:24.462 position:10% line:83% align:start
are reading higher than the
baseline for latent criminals.

00:43:24.496 --> 00:43:26.297 position:21% line:83% align:start
There's no way that
a Psycho-Pass measured

00:43:26.331 --> 00:43:29.334 position:16% line:83% align:start
in a situation like this
will give an accurate number!

00:43:30.568 --> 00:43:32.804 position:21% line:83% align:start
Either we kill them,
or they kill us.

00:43:32.837 --> 00:43:34.539 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh.

00:43:34.572 --> 00:43:35.607 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:43:35.640 --> 00:43:37.909 position:21% line:83% align:start
And like I've said,
this country doesn't exactly

00:43:37.942 --> 00:43:39.811 position:19% line:83% align:start
have the mental health
facilities needed

00:43:39.844 --> 00:43:42.414 position:19% line:89% align:start
to rehabilitate them.

00:43:42.447 --> 00:43:44.249 position:10% line:89% align:start
The only people that remain

00:43:44.282 --> 00:43:46.785 position:21% line:83% align:start
will be those needed
for the new SEAUn.

00:43:46.818 --> 00:43:48.219 position:24% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLA gunts]

00:43:48.253 --> 00:43:49.587 position:21% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLA groaning]

00:43:49.621 --> 00:43:52.490 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
They are... dregs.

00:43:52.524 --> 00:43:54.259 position:13% line:89% align:start
The undesirables left over

00:43:54.292 --> 00:43:57.896 position:21% line:83% align:start
from the great civil
war that they lost.

00:43:57.929 --> 00:43:58.930 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:44:06.938 --> 00:44:09.708 position:33% line:83% align:start
[OPERATOR A]
Skandas activated. Moving out.

00:44:42.941 --> 00:44:45.043 position:10% line:83% align:start
[OPERATOR C] Signal loss on
the comm link with Ganga Two.

00:44:45.077 --> 00:44:47.345 position:5% line:89% align:start
Looks like it's been shot down.

00:44:47.378 --> 00:44:48.413 position:27% line:89% align:start
[NICHOLAS gasps]

00:44:48.446 --> 00:44:49.414 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE gasps]

00:44:49.447 --> 00:44:50.949 position:16% line:83% align:start
[OPERATOR C] Signal loss
with Three and with One!

00:44:50.982 --> 00:44:53.351 position:24% line:83% align:start
Someone's shooting
our birds outta the sky!

00:44:54.652 --> 00:44:56.721 position:21% line:89% align:start
Maybe it's your man.

00:45:09.601 --> 00:45:13.638 position:16% line:83% align:start
Start the counterattack.
Do exactly as I told you.

00:45:17.442 --> 00:45:18.443 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunts]

00:45:22.914 --> 00:45:25.316 position:13% line:83% align:start
[GUERRILLAS] Run! We don't
have much time! Move it!

00:45:26.484 --> 00:45:27.485 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunts]

00:46:25.844 --> 00:46:28.446 position:5% line:83% align:start
[OPERATOR A] We've lost control
of the Ganeshas and Skandas.

00:46:28.479 --> 00:46:31.482 position:21% line:83% align:start
It was right as they
closed in on their targets!

00:46:31.516 --> 00:46:32.784 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
It's not a problem.

00:46:32.817 --> 00:46:34.786 position:24% line:83% align:start
Deactivate all the
Drones and then reboot,

00:46:34.819 --> 00:46:37.422 position:16% line:83% align:start
but I want them switched
into stand-alone mode.

00:46:37.455 --> 00:46:39.824 position:10% line:83% align:start
We won't be able to measure
their Psycho-Passes,

00:46:39.858 --> 00:46:43.027 position:7% line:83% align:start
but as long as we can identify
friend from foe, we'll be fine.

00:46:43.062 --> 00:46:43.962 position:13% line:89% align:start
And what if the guerrillas

00:46:43.995 --> 00:46:46.764 position:24% line:83% align:start
take advantage of
the Drones' down time?

00:46:53.805 --> 00:46:54.806 position:24% line:89% align:start
[OPERATOR B gasps]

00:47:10.455 --> 00:47:11.923 position:21% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLAS yelping]

00:47:11.956 --> 00:47:14.425 position:13% line:83% align:start
[OPERATOR B] All surviving
units have rebooted.

00:47:14.459 --> 00:47:16.661 position:27% line:83% align:start
Good. Start the
counter-attack.

00:47:16.694 --> 00:47:20.099 position:7% line:83% align:start
And send in all reserve units,
except for the guard vehicles.

00:47:26.171 --> 00:47:27.172 position:24% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLA yelps]

00:47:37.249 --> 00:47:42.121 position:16% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLAS whimpering]

00:47:52.497 --> 00:47:54.066 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE gasps]

00:47:54.099 --> 00:47:55.566 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:47:55.600 --> 00:47:57.202 position:24% line:89% align:start
[NICHOLAS grunts]

00:47:57.236 --> 00:47:58.703 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
What are you doing?

00:47:58.736 --> 00:47:59.871 position:16% line:89% align:start
What I came here to do.

00:47:59.904 --> 00:48:01.906 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
You can't go out there alone!

00:48:02.941 --> 00:48:05.743 position:10% line:83% align:start
Hey. I need you to withdraw
your troops right now.

00:48:05.777 --> 00:48:07.179 position:10% line:89% align:start
I'll take the SEAUn forces.

00:48:07.212 --> 00:48:08.913 position:27% line:83% align:start
We've managed to
bloody their noses,

00:48:08.947 --> 00:48:10.815 position:27% line:83% align:start
but we can't let
ourselves get pinned down.

00:48:10.848 --> 00:48:13.085 position:16% line:83% align:start
Otherwise, this'll turn
into a massacre.

00:48:14.552 --> 00:48:19.557 position:24% line:89% align:start
[distant gunfire]

00:48:52.657 --> 00:48:54.959 position:33% line:89% align:start
[clattering]

00:48:54.993 --> 00:48:58.130 position:33% line:89% align:start
[footsteps]

00:49:00.199 --> 00:49:01.200 position:38% line:89% align:start
[sighs]

00:49:02.600 --> 00:49:05.204 position:33% line:89% align:start
[footsteps]

00:49:05.237 --> 00:49:11.976 position:27% line:89% align:start
[BOTH grunting]

00:49:13.678 --> 00:49:15.646 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE grunts]

00:49:23.122 --> 00:49:26.624 position:19% line:83% align:start
It's been a long time,
Mister Kogami.

00:49:43.242 --> 00:49:44.343 position:33% line:89% align:start
Gotta admit.

00:49:44.376 --> 00:49:48.046 position:13% line:83% align:start
I never thought you would
come this far, Inspector.

00:49:48.080 --> 00:49:49.680 position:21% line:89% align:start
You're under arrest.

00:49:50.681 --> 00:49:52.151 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI]
Arrest?

00:49:52.184 --> 00:49:55.019 position:13% line:83% align:start
Haven't you paid attention
to what's happening here?

00:49:56.020 --> 00:49:58.656 position:21% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] We captured
SEAUn terrorists in Japan.

00:49:58.689 --> 00:49:59.991 position:24% line:89% align:start
Did you send them?

00:50:00.024 --> 00:50:02.827 position:21% line:83% align:start
Slow down. What are
you talking about?

00:50:03.828 --> 00:50:05.130 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:50:05.164 --> 00:50:05.963 position:41% line:89% align:start
Wait.

00:50:05.997 --> 00:50:06.898 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunts]

00:50:06.931 --> 00:50:07.698 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE yelps]

00:50:07.732 --> 00:50:08.833 position:33% line:89% align:start
[BOTH grunt]

00:50:08.866 --> 00:50:10.069 position:33% line:89% align:start
[explosion]

00:50:24.383 --> 00:50:25.850 position:19% line:89% align:start
What are you gonna do?

00:50:25.883 --> 00:50:28.287 position:13% line:83% align:start
You can either arrest me,
or let me go.

00:50:28.320 --> 00:50:29.321 position:16% line:89% align:start
Those are your options!

00:50:29.354 --> 00:50:31.156 position:35% line:89% align:start
[panting]

00:50:38.330 --> 00:50:39.164 position:41% line:89% align:start
Jump!

00:50:39.198 --> 00:50:40.199 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunts]

00:50:42.434 --> 00:50:44.936 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE gasps]

00:51:11.330 --> 00:51:12.964 position:21% line:89% align:start
I've made my choice.

00:51:15.200 --> 00:51:17.969 position:24% line:83% align:start
I've decided that
I'm coming with you.

00:51:18.002 --> 00:51:19.071 position:35% line:89% align:start
All right.

00:51:19.104 --> 00:51:22.874 position:16% line:83% align:start
But it's just temporary,
as part of my investigation.

00:51:26.711 --> 00:51:28.913 position:7% line:89% align:start
That's understood, Inspector.

00:51:47.299 --> 00:51:48.966 position:33% line:83% align:start
[OPERATOR A]
Colonel!

00:51:49.000 --> 00:51:50.034 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
From now on,

00:51:50.068 --> 00:51:52.471 position:13% line:83% align:start
make sure the Inspector is
identified as an enemy.

00:51:52.504 --> 00:51:53.771 position:35% line:89% align:start
But sir--

00:51:53.804 --> 00:51:55.440 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
This is a battlefield.

00:51:55.474 --> 00:51:58.076 position:7% line:89% align:start
Nothing will stop our mission.

00:51:58.110 --> 00:51:59.211 position:33% line:83% align:start
[OPERATOR B]
It'll take some time.

00:51:59.244 --> 00:52:01.113 position:13% line:83% align:start
We have to send the system
back to headquarters first

00:52:01.146 --> 00:52:02.080 position:27% line:83% align:start
to get the okay
for reclassification.

00:52:02.114 --> 00:52:04.982 position:21% line:83% align:start
--[NICHOLAS growls]
--Otherwise, we could--

00:52:05.016 --> 00:52:08.153 position:13% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI] Bullet wounds to
abdomen. No abdominal hernia.

00:52:08.187 --> 00:52:12.491 position:5% line:83% align:start
Pelvis, normal. Pubic symphysis,
normal. Lumbar spine, normal.

00:52:12.524 --> 00:52:13.292 position:24% line:89% align:start
[GUERILLA groans]

00:52:13.325 --> 00:52:17.262 position:24% line:83% align:start
Femoral is normal.
Limbs, normal.

00:52:18.297 --> 00:52:19.897 position:21% line:89% align:start
Gimme a neck brace.

00:52:26.305 --> 00:52:27.905 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunts]

00:52:27.939 --> 00:52:29.941 position:13% line:89% align:start
[GUERILLA whimpers, yelps]

00:52:29.974 --> 00:52:34.379 position:21% line:89% align:start
[GUERILLA groaning]

00:52:37.848 --> 00:52:40.285 position:7% line:89% align:start
Load up. We gotta keep moving.

00:52:45.823 --> 00:52:46.692 position:30% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI sighs]

00:52:49.927 --> 00:52:51.430 position:21% line:83% align:start
What are you really
doing here, Kogami?

00:52:51.463 --> 00:52:53.065 position:19% line:89% align:start
And be honest with me.

00:53:07.812 --> 00:53:10.215 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI]
What's it looks like I'm doing?

00:53:10.249 --> 00:53:11.183 position:21% line:89% align:start
I'm helping to bring

00:53:11.216 --> 00:53:13.918 position:24% line:83% align:start
real democracy and
freedom to this country.

00:53:20.459 --> 00:53:23.060 position:16% line:83% align:start
So, after this mission,
what's your next move?

00:53:24.028 --> 00:53:26.030 position:5% line:89% align:start
Back to the guerrilla basecamp.

00:53:35.607 --> 00:53:37.376 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI]
By the way, Inspector.

00:53:39.010 --> 00:53:41.146 position:7% line:89% align:start
Come on. Stop calling me that.

00:53:43.315 --> 00:53:46.151 position:21% line:83% align:start
All right. Have you
met Chairman Hang?

00:53:46.184 --> 00:53:49.488 position:24% line:83% align:start
Oh, yeah. I talked
to him yesterday.

00:53:49.521 --> 00:53:52.457 position:10% line:83% align:start
And? Don't you think there's
something strange there?

00:53:52.491 --> 00:53:54.293 position:41% line:89% align:start
What?

00:53:54.326 --> 00:53:56.328 position:16% line:83% align:start
I wonder what his Crime
Coefficient would be

00:53:56.361 --> 00:54:00.465 position:24% line:83% align:start
if we scanned him.
After all, he's a dictator.

00:54:02.867 --> 00:54:04.236 position:41% line:83% align:start
[HANG]
So the mission was a failure

00:54:04.269 --> 00:54:08.340 position:13% line:83% align:start
and our Japanese Inspector
Tsunemori is missing?

00:54:08.373 --> 00:54:10.208 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
Her conduct was tantamount

00:54:10.242 --> 00:54:12.009 position:13% line:89% align:start
to aiding the guerrillas.

00:54:12.043 --> 00:54:15.514 position:21% line:83% align:start
She acted completely
without authorization!

00:54:15.547 --> 00:54:16.448 position:41% line:83% align:start
[HANG]
Be that as it may,

00:54:16.481 --> 00:54:19.217 position:24% line:83% align:start
she was a foreign
guest in your custody.

00:54:19.251 --> 00:54:22.387 position:24% line:83% align:start
This is a question
of responsibility.

00:54:22.421 --> 00:54:24.156 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
But, sir.

00:54:24.189 --> 00:54:26.258 position:41% line:83% align:start
[HANG]
Relax. I'm joking!

00:54:26.291 --> 00:54:27.626 position:5% line:89% align:start
The Japanese government's aware

00:54:27.659 --> 00:54:30.195 position:7% line:83% align:start
of the civil turmoil currently
affecting our country.

00:54:30.228 --> 00:54:32.863 position:13% line:83% align:start
They wouldn't have sent a
young female Inspector alone

00:54:32.897 --> 00:54:34.433 position:7% line:89% align:start
into the middle of a warzone,

00:54:34.466 --> 00:54:37.069 position:24% line:83% align:start
if her life really
mattered to them.

00:54:37.102 --> 00:54:40.639 position:19% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS] Still, this
situation is regrettable.

00:54:40.672 --> 00:54:43.075 position:10% line:83% align:start
Of course, the other way to
look at this is that she's going

00:54:43.108 --> 00:54:46.078 position:7% line:83% align:start
to cause us even more trouble
in the days to come, Colonel.

00:54:46.111 --> 00:54:47.346 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
What?

00:54:47.379 --> 00:54:49.880 position:7% line:83% align:start
[HANG] It's entirely possible
that the Japanese sent her here

00:54:49.914 --> 00:54:51.949 position:13% line:83% align:start
because they're confident
she can survive

00:54:51.982 --> 00:54:55.554 position:7% line:83% align:start
in conditions like our little
guerrilla warfare problem.

00:54:55.587 --> 00:54:59.124 position:19% line:83% align:start
I'm very interested in
seeing how this plays out.

00:55:11.136 --> 00:55:16.974 position:35% line:89% align:start
[ringing]

00:55:22.114 --> 00:55:24.249 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
I have an urgent job for you.

00:55:24.282 --> 00:55:26.685 position:21% line:83% align:start
Of course, I'll make
it worth your while.

00:55:26.718 --> 00:55:28.387 position:10% line:89% align:start
I'm very grateful, Nicholas.

00:55:28.420 --> 00:55:31.956 position:19% line:83% align:start
We have more time than
we know what to do with.

00:55:31.989 --> 00:55:34.359 position:13% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS] Near Siem Reap,
there's a guerrilla stronghold

00:55:34.393 --> 00:55:37.195 position:21% line:83% align:start
currently harboring
two Japanese citizens.

00:55:37.229 --> 00:55:38.929 position:7% line:89% align:start
One is a member of the group.

00:55:38.963 --> 00:55:40.465 position:16% line:83% align:start
The other, an Inspector
from Tokyo,

00:55:40.499 --> 00:55:42.667 position:5% line:89% align:start
who was sent here to arrest him.

00:55:42.701 --> 00:55:45.537 position:5% line:89% align:start
I want them both taken care of.

00:55:45.570 --> 00:55:46.605 position:13% line:89% align:start
The guerrilla's one thing,

00:55:46.638 --> 00:55:49.441 position:13% line:83% align:start
but an Inspector presents
all sorts of problems.

00:55:49.474 --> 00:55:53.145 position:10% line:83% align:start
You honestly think killing a
Japanese agent is a smart play?

00:55:53.178 --> 00:55:55.580 position:16% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS] She looks as
though she may get in the way.

00:55:55.614 --> 00:55:57.516 position:27% line:89% align:start
She's a hazard.

00:55:57.549 --> 00:55:59.084 position:33% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA]
Here we go.

00:56:00.452 --> 00:56:02.487 position:19% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA] Since you
got involved with Sibyl,

00:56:02.521 --> 00:56:05.223 position:30% line:83% align:start
all we get are
messy jobs like this.

00:56:09.261 --> 00:56:10.695 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
It's thanks to Sibyl

00:56:10.729 --> 00:56:13.532 position:13% line:83% align:start
that we have this paradise
we call Shambhala.

00:56:13.565 --> 00:56:16.000 position:10% line:83% align:start
Even someone like you could
live a civilized life here,

00:56:16.033 --> 00:56:18.035 position:30% line:83% align:start
if you wanted.
How much longer do you plan

00:56:18.069 --> 00:56:21.273 position:10% line:83% align:start
to continue playing savages
on your little island?

00:56:23.208 --> 00:56:24.709 position:33% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA]
At the level of the individual,

00:56:24.743 --> 00:56:27.412 position:30% line:83% align:start
violence has a
detoxifying effect.

00:56:27.446 --> 00:56:29.648 position:24% line:83% align:start
It takes away the
inferiority complexes

00:56:29.681 --> 00:56:31.183 position:7% line:89% align:start
and changes the contemplative

00:56:31.216 --> 00:56:33.951 position:16% line:83% align:start
and desperate attitudes
of native people.

00:56:34.753 --> 00:56:36.755 position:33% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA]
Their self-worth.

00:56:36.788 --> 00:56:38.989 position:19% line:83% align:start
Violence has the power
to make them fearless

00:56:39.023 --> 00:56:40.091 position:16% line:89% align:start
and, in their own eyes,

00:56:40.125 --> 00:56:42.527 position:21% line:83% align:start
restores the dignity
that's been stolen from them.

00:56:42.561 --> 00:56:43.728 position:27% line:89% align:start
[NICHOLAS sighs]

00:56:43.762 --> 00:56:46.164 position:13% line:83% align:start
What, you're not familiar
with the work of Frantz Fanon?

00:56:46.198 --> 00:56:48.233 position:7% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS] We're investigating
the precise whereabouts

00:56:48.266 --> 00:56:51.269 position:16% line:83% align:start
of the targets. As soon
as we find them--

00:56:51.303 --> 00:56:52.504 position:10% line:89% align:start
Yeah, don't worry about it.

00:56:52.537 --> 00:56:54.539 position:16% line:83% align:start
We mercenaries have our
own intelligence network

00:56:54.573 --> 00:56:56.174 position:21% line:89% align:start
that we can utilize.

00:56:56.208 --> 00:56:59.211 position:7% line:83% align:start
Most information can be bought
with money or valuables.

00:56:59.244 --> 00:57:00.745 position:5% line:89% align:start
Of course, I'll have to bill you

00:57:00.779 --> 00:57:04.115 position:24% line:83% align:start
for the necessary
expenses separately.

00:57:04.149 --> 00:57:05.183 position:35% line:89% align:start
All right?

00:57:05.217 --> 00:57:06.251 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
No problem.

00:57:06.284 --> 00:57:09.621 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'm gonna need military
aircraft ground clearance

00:57:09.654 --> 00:57:12.157 position:13% line:89% align:start
and IFF recognition codes.

00:58:05.677 --> 00:58:08.480 position:13% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] There are children
and elderly here, too?

00:58:12.117 --> 00:58:14.051 position:13% line:89% align:start
Good, you're back, Kogami.

00:58:21.860 --> 00:58:22.961 position:33% line:89% align:start
Who is she?

00:58:22.994 --> 00:58:25.764 position:13% line:83% align:start
It's a long story, but all
you need to know is this:

00:58:25.797 --> 00:58:27.532 position:21% line:89% align:start
she's not our enemy.

00:58:27.566 --> 00:58:30.068 position:13% line:89% align:start
Trust me. She's my guest.

00:58:31.703 --> 00:58:36.374 position:7% line:83% align:start
Hmm. Kogami must have offered
guidance to you, as well.

00:58:36.408 --> 00:58:38.810 position:10% line:89% align:start
Guess we're comrades, then.

00:58:38.843 --> 00:58:43.448 position:16% line:83% align:start
My name is Sem. I'm the
leader of this group here.

00:58:43.481 --> 00:58:47.118 position:16% line:83% align:start
And I'm Akane Tsunemori.
Nice to meet you.

00:58:47.152 --> 00:58:51.523 position:24% line:83% align:start
We sustained more
casualties today. I'm sorry.

00:58:51.556 --> 00:58:55.660 position:13% line:83% align:start
No. If it weren't for you,
we'd all be dead.

00:59:07.539 --> 00:59:10.375 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI]
Hey, how's Gino these days?

00:59:10.408 --> 00:59:13.178 position:21% line:83% align:start
After what happened,
he became an Enforcer.

00:59:14.212 --> 00:59:15.347 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI]
I see.

00:59:16.314 --> 00:59:17.916 position:21% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] But what are
you doing here, Kogami?

00:59:17.949 --> 00:59:20.752 position:19% line:89% align:start
In a place like this?

00:59:20.785 --> 00:59:23.555 position:13% line:83% align:start
First, I was just lookin'
for somewhere quiet.

00:59:30.862 --> 00:59:32.464 position:27% line:89% align:start
I was exhausted.

00:59:32.497 --> 00:59:35.467 position:13% line:83% align:start
But once I strayed outside
the Sibyl System's reach,

00:59:35.500 --> 00:59:38.803 position:13% line:83% align:start
just couldn't find peace,
no matter where I went.

00:59:38.837 --> 00:59:42.374 position:16% line:83% align:start
Only war and destruction
all across the world.

00:59:42.407 --> 00:59:44.309 position:13% line:83% align:start
I thought that I'd trained
myself pretty well,

00:59:44.342 --> 00:59:48.380 position:10% line:83% align:start
but it opened my eyes... to
just how soft I really was.

00:59:48.413 --> 00:59:51.583 position:16% line:83% align:start
So I learned to survive.
For real this time.

00:59:52.584 --> 00:59:55.220 position:21% line:83% align:start
So then why did you
join these guerrillas?

00:59:57.656 --> 01:00:00.258 position:13% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI] Not long after I
arrived here in this country,

01:00:00.291 --> 01:00:02.594 position:21% line:83% align:start
Hang established his
self-serving regime,

01:00:02.627 --> 01:00:04.929 position:19% line:83% align:start
and the Drones started
hunting down guerrillas.

01:00:07.666 --> 01:00:11.536 position:10% line:83% align:start
So, I decided I'd teach the
guerrillas how to fight back.

01:00:13.571 --> 01:00:15.940 position:24% line:83% align:start
All of the Drones
are made in Japan.

01:00:15.974 --> 01:00:17.409 position:5% line:89% align:start
I know what their weaknesses are

01:00:17.442 --> 01:00:20.445 position:16% line:83% align:start
and how to exploit them
to bring 'em down.

01:00:23.648 --> 01:00:24.482 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
But...

01:00:24.516 --> 01:00:25.817 position:24% line:83% align:start
...what is it you
hope to accomplish

01:00:25.850 --> 01:00:27.886 position:16% line:89% align:start
by helping these people?

01:00:27.919 --> 01:00:29.888 position:16% line:89% align:start
It may not look it now,

01:00:29.921 --> 01:00:32.891 position:16% line:83% align:start
but we thought we had a
chance to gain the upper hand.

01:00:36.594 --> 01:00:39.664 position:5% line:83% align:start
Although, Hang has bestowed upon
himself the title of Chairman,

01:00:39.698 --> 01:00:41.766 position:21% line:83% align:start
in truth, the guy's
nothing but a dictator,

01:00:41.800 --> 01:00:44.402 position:19% line:89% align:start
just a common warlord.

01:00:44.436 --> 01:00:48.006 position:10% line:83% align:start
In an effort to outmaneuver
all his political rivals,

01:00:48.039 --> 01:00:50.942 position:19% line:83% align:start
he joined forces with
Japan's Sibyl System.

01:00:53.445 --> 01:00:54.612 position:38% line:89% align:start
[groans]

01:00:54.646 --> 01:00:56.781 position:13% line:89% align:start
It was all a smokescreen.

01:00:56.815 --> 01:00:59.884 position:21% line:83% align:start
He never cared about
building a paradise.

01:01:12.464 --> 01:01:14.365 position:10% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI] With Sibyl's help,
Hang's faction rose

01:01:14.399 --> 01:01:16.601 position:30% line:83% align:start
to become the
predominant military force,

01:01:16.634 --> 01:01:18.937 position:27% line:83% align:start
overwhelming the
other warlords.

01:01:18.970 --> 01:01:22.273 position:19% line:83% align:start
We thought this would
ultimately lead to his downfall.

01:01:22.307 --> 01:01:27.378 position:10% line:83% align:start
See, the Sibyl System is an
extreme form of bureaucracy.

01:01:27.412 --> 01:01:30.849 position:19% line:83% align:start
For a dictator, it can
be a total nightmare.

01:01:30.882 --> 01:01:32.951 position:21% line:83% align:start
Sure, he may try to
govern on his own,

01:01:32.984 --> 01:01:35.620 position:10% line:83% align:start
but everything's controlled
by the system,

01:01:35.653 --> 01:01:37.856 position:7% line:89% align:start
leaving him no real authority.

01:01:38.957 --> 01:01:40.725 position:19% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI] We figured it
was only a matter of time

01:01:40.759 --> 01:01:43.995 position:13% line:83% align:start
before Hang realized this,
and that when he did,

01:01:44.028 --> 01:01:45.630 position:5% line:89% align:start
he would abandon Shambhala Float

01:01:45.663 --> 01:01:48.533 position:27% line:83% align:start
before they even
finished construction.

01:01:48.566 --> 01:01:51.503 position:7% line:83% align:start
At least, that was our opinion
till about a year ago.

01:01:52.504 --> 01:01:55.673 position:7% line:89% align:start
I see. So Hang surprised you.

01:01:57.542 --> 01:01:58.543 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI]
Yeah.

01:02:00.845 --> 01:02:01.780 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI]
He surrendered control

01:02:01.813 --> 01:02:04.549 position:19% line:83% align:start
over to Sibyl without
putting up a fight.

01:02:04.582 --> 01:02:08.419 position:16% line:83% align:start
Built his utopia on the
sea reminiscent of Japan,

01:02:08.453 --> 01:02:10.722 position:19% line:83% align:start
and he's still got the
armed Drones going around,

01:02:10.755 --> 01:02:13.558 position:27% line:83% align:start
slaughtering the
rebels without mercy.

01:02:18.530 --> 01:02:23.535 position:24% line:89% align:start
[PRIEST chanting]

01:02:29.007 --> 01:02:34.012 position:21% line:89% align:start
[chanting continues]

01:02:37.015 --> 01:02:40.552 position:21% line:89% align:start
[chanting continues]

01:02:40.585 --> 01:02:43.021 position:13% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI] There's gotta be
something more going on here.

01:02:43.054 --> 01:02:46.758 position:13% line:83% align:start
Something between Hang and
Sibyl we're still unaware of.

01:02:46.791 --> 01:02:49.661 position:19% line:83% align:start
And until I can figure
out just what it is,

01:02:49.694 --> 01:02:51.362 position:24% line:89% align:start
I won't back down.

01:02:52.164 --> 01:02:55.033 position:19% line:83% align:start
So, then what, is that
your idea of justice?

01:02:55.067 --> 01:02:58.070 position:16% line:83% align:start
Operating out there all
on your own as a vigilante,

01:02:58.103 --> 01:02:59.671 position:24% line:83% align:start
bypassing the law
without concern

01:02:59.704 --> 01:03:01.406 position:13% line:89% align:start
for who you drag into it?

01:03:02.640 --> 01:03:05.144 position:7% line:89% align:start
You sure don't hold back now.

01:03:05.177 --> 01:03:07.645 position:16% line:83% align:start
Yeah, well, you haven't
changed at all.

01:03:07.679 --> 01:03:10.481 position:16% line:89% align:start
And... that's a relief.

01:03:15.987 --> 01:03:18.389 position:16% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] So, you honestly
had nothing to do

01:03:18.423 --> 01:03:21.526 position:13% line:83% align:start
with those terrorists who
came over to Japan to attack?

01:03:21.559 --> 01:03:22.760 position:21% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI] We may have
had a couple of guys

01:03:22.794 --> 01:03:24.762 position:30% line:83% align:start
who wanted to
retaliate against Japan

01:03:24.796 --> 01:03:27.066 position:10% line:89% align:start
as the birthplace of Sibyl.

01:03:27.099 --> 01:03:29.500 position:16% line:83% align:start
But when both Sem and I
objected to their proposal,

01:03:29.534 --> 01:03:31.103 position:16% line:89% align:start
they all left this camp.

01:03:33.004 --> 01:03:34.706 position:24% line:83% align:start
None of those guys
would have been capable

01:03:34.739 --> 01:03:37.109 position:19% line:83% align:start
of arranging overseas
travel on their own.

01:03:41.946 --> 01:03:46.185 position:24% line:83% align:start
Yeah, that's them.
Samrin, Ma, and Sim.

01:03:46.218 --> 01:03:48.120 position:33% line:89% align:start
No question.

01:03:48.153 --> 01:03:50.588 position:16% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] They were using
high-level cracking devices

01:03:50.622 --> 01:03:51.589 position:19% line:89% align:start
and even had some way

01:03:51.623 --> 01:03:54.792 position:19% line:83% align:start
of contacting a fence
in the abolition block.

01:03:56.895 --> 01:03:58.630 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Don't you find that odd?

01:03:59.864 --> 01:04:01.432 position:24% line:89% align:start
Yeah, definitely.

01:04:01.466 --> 01:04:04.969 position:13% line:83% align:start
We have to assume they got
help from someone else.

01:04:07.038 --> 01:04:08.473 position:33% line:83% align:start
[GUERRILLA]
Kogami.

01:04:08.506 --> 01:04:09.974 position:30% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI sighs]

01:04:10.008 --> 01:04:12.077 position:21% line:89% align:start
Hell of a situation.

01:04:12.111 --> 01:04:14.146 position:19% line:83% align:start
We've both waded into
a much deeper swamp

01:04:14.179 --> 01:04:16.781 position:24% line:83% align:start
than either of us
could've anticipated.

01:04:21.686 --> 01:04:23.588 position:19% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI] Why don't you
spend the night here?

01:04:23.621 --> 01:04:24.889 position:5% line:89% align:start
I can have somebody drop you off

01:04:24.923 --> 01:04:27.492 position:21% line:83% align:start
near Shambhala Float
in the morning.

01:04:27.525 --> 01:04:30.028 position:5% line:83% align:start
As long as you behave yourself,
no one will hurt you.

01:04:31.629 --> 01:04:34.732 position:13% line:83% align:start
Should I bother asking you
to come with me voluntarily?

01:04:34.766 --> 01:04:35.800 position:24% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI chuckles]

01:04:35.833 --> 01:04:37.035 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI]
Whatever you do,

01:04:37.069 --> 01:04:40.205 position:10% line:83% align:start
just don't tell Sem and the
others you're a detective, okay?

01:04:40.239 --> 01:04:42.507 position:16% line:83% align:start
They find out you're on
the government side,

01:04:42.540 --> 01:04:44.609 position:24% line:83% align:start
they'll be forced
to take action.

01:05:22.580 --> 01:05:25.616 position:21% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLA groaning]

01:05:30.322 --> 01:05:32.257 position:21% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLA grunting]

01:05:32.291 --> 01:05:34.892 position:21% line:89% align:start
[GUERILLA groaning]

01:05:45.237 --> 01:05:46.238 position:24% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLA groans]

01:05:47.905 --> 01:05:49.241 position:24% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLA yelps]

01:05:55.080 --> 01:05:56.748 position:19% line:89% align:start
We're all clear here.

01:06:02.121 --> 01:06:03.688 position:33% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA]
Let's get moving.

01:06:03.721 --> 01:06:04.722 position:33% line:83% align:start
[BABANGIDA]
Roger that.

01:06:04.756 --> 01:06:05.823 position:38% line:83% align:start
[WEBER]
Roger that.

01:06:41.726 --> 01:06:42.927 position:30% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI sighs]

01:06:50.269 --> 01:06:52.271 position:24% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] One of the
terrorists who came to Japan

01:06:52.304 --> 01:06:54.572 position:5% line:89% align:start
had a rare paper book with him.

01:06:55.706 --> 01:06:59.644 position:10% line:83% align:start
The French novel "In Search
of Lost Time" by Proust.

01:06:59.677 --> 01:07:02.147 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI]
Probably my personal copy.

01:07:02.181 --> 01:07:07.086 position:21% line:83% align:start
Before Samrin left,
he expressed interest.

01:07:07.119 --> 01:07:09.687 position:30% line:83% align:start
All this time,
I thought I'd lost it,

01:07:09.720 --> 01:07:12.224 position:21% line:83% align:start
but I guess he just
took it with him.

01:07:12.257 --> 01:07:14.625 position:10% line:89% align:start
That man, Sem, from earlier,

01:07:14.659 --> 01:07:17.995 position:10% line:83% align:start
he said something about you
offering guidance, didn't he?

01:07:18.029 --> 01:07:19.164 position:13% line:89% align:start
Which leads me to believe

01:07:19.198 --> 01:07:21.799 position:24% line:83% align:start
you're more than a
mere strategic advisor.

01:07:21.833 --> 01:07:25.036 position:13% line:83% align:start
They see you as kind of a
spiritual mentor, as well.

01:07:26.771 --> 01:07:30.741 position:7% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI] To be honest, I wish
they wouldn't. That isn't me.

01:07:30.775 --> 01:07:33.212 position:24% line:83% align:start
But despite that,
it seems the people here

01:07:33.245 --> 01:07:36.981 position:7% line:83% align:start
are perhaps overly influenced
by everything I say and do.

01:07:38.049 --> 01:07:40.751 position:19% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] It may not be
intentional on your part,

01:07:40.785 --> 01:07:43.788 position:13% line:83% align:start
but you do have a sort of
irresistible magnetism

01:07:43.821 --> 01:07:46.091 position:19% line:89% align:start
that draws people in.

01:07:46.125 --> 01:07:49.194 position:27% line:83% align:start
Similar to what
Shogo Makishima had.

01:07:49.228 --> 01:07:50.395 position:30% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI sighs]

01:07:50.429 --> 01:07:51.729 position:38% line:89% align:start
So what?

01:07:51.762 --> 01:07:54.832 position:19% line:83% align:start
Do you see me as being
the same as him?

01:07:54.866 --> 01:07:55.933 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
You were better than anyone

01:07:55.967 --> 01:07:57.668 position:24% line:83% align:start
at getting inside
Makishima's head

01:07:57.702 --> 01:07:59.937 position:7% line:89% align:start
and predicting his next move.

01:07:59.971 --> 01:08:01.106 position:5% line:89% align:start
Would it really be so surprising

01:08:01.140 --> 01:08:05.110 position:13% line:83% align:start
if you shared some of his
talents and characteristics?

01:08:05.144 --> 01:08:07.778 position:19% line:83% align:start
Maybe, except for back
when I was in Japan,

01:08:07.812 --> 01:08:09.046 position:5% line:89% align:start
my words were never responsible

01:08:09.081 --> 01:08:12.217 position:21% line:83% align:start
for leading anybody
astray, were they?

01:08:12.251 --> 01:08:14.886 position:21% line:83% align:start
So why is everything
different now?

01:08:16.188 --> 01:08:18.756 position:19% line:83% align:start
Because your situation
is different now.

01:08:20.392 --> 01:08:23.262 position:16% line:83% align:start
I don't know if you even
realize it, Kogami,

01:08:23.295 --> 01:08:25.897 position:19% line:83% align:start
but the position that
you find yourself in here

01:08:25.930 --> 01:08:29.134 position:16% line:83% align:start
is a lot like how Shogo
Makishima started out.

01:08:30.335 --> 01:08:31.769 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI]
Are you saying,

01:08:31.802 --> 01:08:34.705 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'm destined to wind up
like Makishima?

01:08:34.739 --> 01:08:36.275 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
No.

01:08:36.308 --> 01:08:39.311 position:16% line:83% align:start
But, I think there will
be more and more people

01:08:39.344 --> 01:08:44.048 position:10% line:83% align:start
who will want you to embody
the same traits Makishima did.

01:08:44.082 --> 01:08:46.951 position:13% line:83% align:start
Those who harbor anger and
resentment towards society

01:08:46.984 --> 01:08:50.255 position:5% line:83% align:start
will expect something from you,
and trust in you to lead them.

01:08:50.289 --> 01:08:52.890 position:16% line:83% align:start
You have such an ability
to draw people in,

01:08:52.924 --> 01:08:56.027 position:7% line:83% align:start
they might put you on the same
pedestal Makishima was on.

01:08:56.894 --> 01:08:59.264 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI]
That would be annoying.

01:08:59.298 --> 01:09:00.465 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
On the other hand,

01:09:00.499 --> 01:09:04.102 position:10% line:83% align:start
at least you don't share his
ambition to control people.

01:09:04.136 --> 01:09:08.140 position:5% line:83% align:start
And that's, probably the biggest
difference between you and him.

01:09:09.274 --> 01:09:10.275 position:30% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI sighs]

01:09:12.043 --> 01:09:14.845 position:10% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI] If that's what you
think was driving Makishima,

01:09:14.879 --> 01:09:17.449 position:10% line:83% align:start
it's no wonder you guys had
such a hard time with him.

01:09:18.383 --> 01:09:19.218 position:33% line:89% align:start
[gun fires]

01:09:19.251 --> 01:09:22.387 position:16% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI, AKANE gasping]

01:09:26.458 --> 01:09:27.925 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunts]

01:09:32.231 --> 01:09:35.434 position:10% line:83% align:start
[GUARD] Enemy attack! Flames
rising from Bayon's direction!

01:09:35.467 --> 01:09:38.836 position:10% line:83% align:start
Enemy attack! Flames rising
from Bayon's direction!

01:09:46.811 --> 01:09:48.946 position:13% line:89% align:start
Acquiring target position.

01:09:55.120 --> 01:09:56.121 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

01:09:57.122 --> 01:10:00.125 position:21% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLAS yelling]

01:10:04.229 --> 01:10:06.265 position:19% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLAS grunting]

01:10:06.298 --> 01:10:08.833 position:21% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLAS yelping]

01:10:10.235 --> 01:10:13.838 position:24% line:83% align:start
Weber. Babangida.
Keep pushing forward.

01:10:13.871 --> 01:10:14.872 position:24% line:83% align:start
[WEBER, BABANGIDA]
Copy that.

01:10:16.941 --> 01:10:17.942 position:24% line:89% align:start
[RUTAGANDA grunts]

01:10:19.877 --> 01:10:23.881 position:21% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLAS chatter]

01:10:28.320 --> 01:10:30.921 position:7% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLAS gasping, yelping]

01:10:32.857 --> 01:10:35.327 position:21% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLA groaning]

01:10:35.360 --> 01:10:39.464 position:21% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILLA groaning]

01:10:39.498 --> 01:10:42.100 position:27% line:83% align:start
Yulia, have you
located the target yet?

01:10:42.134 --> 01:10:43.368 position:38% line:83% align:start
[YULIA]
No, sir.

01:10:43.402 --> 01:10:45.002 position:24% line:89% align:start
[GUERRILA grunts]

01:10:45.036 --> 01:10:46.204 position:33% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA]
Damn!

01:10:46.238 --> 01:10:49.207 position:10% line:83% align:start
These amateur peons are even
weaker than I was expecting.

01:10:49.241 --> 01:10:50.841 position:21% line:89% align:start
Bun, are you there?

01:10:52.144 --> 01:10:54.479 position:13% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA] That's enough.
Search for the target.

01:10:55.913 --> 01:10:56.981 position:41% line:83% align:start
[BUN]
Roger.

01:11:03.121 --> 01:11:05.890 position:10% line:89% align:start
[CROWD shouting, whimpering]

01:11:05.923 --> 01:11:07.192 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunts]

01:11:07.225 --> 01:11:09.994 position:24% line:83% align:start
These guys aren't
attacking like the military!

01:11:10.027 --> 01:11:11.496 position:16% line:89% align:start
How are they different?

01:11:11.530 --> 01:11:12.631 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI]
Prob'ly special forces

01:11:12.664 --> 01:11:15.966 position:13% line:83% align:start
with combat training that
doesn't depend on Drones.

01:11:16.000 --> 01:11:18.103 position:7% line:89% align:start
Got a bad feeling about this.

01:11:21.440 --> 01:11:22.574 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI]
Sem!

01:11:22.607 --> 01:11:24.176 position:27% line:89% align:start
Where's the ECM?

01:11:24.209 --> 01:11:25.943 position:13% line:89% align:start
They have the device now!

01:11:25.976 --> 01:11:28.113 position:24% line:83% align:start
Those bastards are
one step ahead of us!

01:11:28.146 --> 01:11:29.348 position:44% line:89% align:start
Sem!

01:11:29.381 --> 01:11:31.849 position:10% line:83% align:start
--We gotta help her escape!
--[AKANE gasps]

01:11:35.087 --> 01:11:36.254 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Kogami, wait!

01:11:36.288 --> 01:11:38.256 position:5% line:89% align:start
I want you to get out, at least.

01:11:38.290 --> 01:11:39.890 position:10% line:89% align:start
We'll try and keep 'em busy.

01:11:39.924 --> 01:11:41.660 position:24% line:83% align:start
What? No, I'm not
leaving you behind!

01:11:41.693 --> 01:11:43.362 position:10% line:89% align:start
Continue the investigation!

01:11:43.395 --> 01:11:45.664 position:19% line:83% align:start
You could uncover the
truth about Chairman Hang!

01:11:45.697 --> 01:11:47.466 position:27% line:83% align:start
Which might just
give us a chance.

01:11:47.499 --> 01:11:50.135 position:27% line:83% align:start
Get to Shambhala
and keep digging!

01:11:50.168 --> 01:11:50.968 position:41% line:89% align:start
But--

01:11:51.001 --> 01:11:52.104 position:19% line:89% align:start
Don't worry 'bout me.

01:11:52.137 --> 01:11:54.606 position:13% line:83% align:start
Come on, you really think
I'll go down that easily?

01:11:55.973 --> 01:11:59.043 position:19% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI] And you gotta
survive this, too, Akane.

01:11:59.077 --> 01:12:01.346 position:7% line:89% align:start
How else you gonna arrest me?

01:12:01.380 --> 01:12:03.081 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hm.

01:12:03.115 --> 01:12:05.150 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

01:12:05.183 --> 01:12:06.251 position:41% line:89% align:start
Okay.

01:12:42.187 --> 01:12:43.053 position:44% line:89% align:start
Sem!

01:12:43.088 --> 01:12:45.022 position:21% line:89% align:start
Run, Kogami! Hurry!

01:12:52.997 --> 01:12:54.399 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI]
Sem! Get out of there!

01:12:54.433 --> 01:12:56.668 position:24% line:83% align:start
I won't abandon a
friend like that!

01:12:59.204 --> 01:13:00.605 position:24% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunting]

01:13:00.639 --> 01:13:03.275 position:21% line:83% align:start
--[GUERRILLA grunts]
--[SEM] No! Hang on!

01:13:03.308 --> 01:13:04.609 position:44% line:89% align:start
Sem!

01:13:11.516 --> 01:13:14.486 position:24% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunting]

01:13:17.222 --> 01:13:18.223 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunts]

01:13:22.561 --> 01:13:25.430 position:24% line:83% align:start
[BUN] Target Delta
identified. Opening fire!

01:13:25.464 --> 01:13:28.300 position:21% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA] Hold on.
What about Target Juliet?

01:13:28.333 --> 01:13:29.534 position:33% line:89% align:start
[explosion]

01:13:48.353 --> 01:13:51.189 position:33% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA]
Signal lost. She's getting away.

01:13:52.157 --> 01:13:53.658 position:41% line:83% align:start
[BUN]
Do you want me to chase her?

01:13:53.692 --> 01:13:55.360 position:33% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA]
No, it's too late.

01:13:55.393 --> 01:13:57.662 position:21% line:83% align:start
Capture Delta alive
instead. Don't kill him.

01:13:57.696 --> 01:13:59.598 position:21% line:89% align:start
I'll be right there.

01:13:59.631 --> 01:14:00.632 position:41% line:83% align:start
[BUN]
Understood.

01:14:02.701 --> 01:14:03.602 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunts]

01:14:03.635 --> 01:14:04.736 position:30% line:89% align:start
[YULIA grunts]

01:14:04.769 --> 01:14:07.772 position:24% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunting]

01:14:07.806 --> 01:14:09.107 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

01:14:09.140 --> 01:14:10.141 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunts]

01:14:12.077 --> 01:14:15.380 position:24% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunting]

01:14:15.413 --> 01:14:17.282 position:30% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI yelps]

01:14:17.315 --> 01:14:21.720 position:19% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI, BUN grunting]

01:14:21.753 --> 01:14:22.754 position:30% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI gasps]

01:14:28.360 --> 01:14:31.061 position:24% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunting]

01:14:31.863 --> 01:14:36.134 position:24% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunting]

01:14:36.167 --> 01:14:37.569 position:27% line:83% align:start
--[KOGAMI yelps]
--[RUTAGANDA grunts]

01:14:37.602 --> 01:14:39.337 position:24% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI groaning]

01:14:39.371 --> 01:14:42.173 position:33% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA]
You're really something.

01:14:42.207 --> 01:14:42.874 position:30% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI gasps]

01:14:42.908 --> 01:14:44.476 position:5% line:89% align:start
If you don't finish me off now,

01:14:44.509 --> 01:14:46.611 position:24% line:83% align:start
you're only going
to regret it later.

01:14:46.645 --> 01:14:47.746 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI groans]

01:14:47.779 --> 01:14:50.482 position:7% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA] Well as terrifying
as you make that sound,

01:14:50.515 --> 01:14:53.652 position:19% line:83% align:start
we have some important
questions to ask you.

01:15:08.233 --> 01:15:10.335 position:16% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS] You may be an
important guest here, Inspector,

01:15:10.368 --> 01:15:13.638 position:10% line:83% align:start
but there are limits to our
patience and hospitality.

01:15:13.672 --> 01:15:16.608 position:24% line:83% align:start
Oh, really, I'm an
important guest?

01:15:16.641 --> 01:15:18.710 position:27% line:83% align:start
Is that why you
tried to kill me?

01:15:18.743 --> 01:15:21.780 position:13% line:83% align:start
We had no choice. You were
working with the guerrillas.

01:15:21.813 --> 01:15:24.182 position:19% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] That was part
of my investigation.

01:15:24.215 --> 01:15:26.117 position:10% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS] It would be wise
to recognize the fact

01:15:26.151 --> 01:15:28.853 position:13% line:83% align:start
that you're in our country
now and under our rules.

01:15:28.887 --> 01:15:31.690 position:7% line:83% align:start
We'll be deporting you back to
Japan on the next flight out.

01:15:31.723 --> 01:15:35.160 position:5% line:83% align:start
You can keep those cuffs around
your wrists as a souvenir.

01:15:41.833 --> 01:15:42.867 position:41% line:83% align:start
[HANG]
Colonel.

01:15:42.901 --> 01:15:44.669 position:16% line:83% align:start
You know better than to
make a decision like this

01:15:44.703 --> 01:15:47.205 position:10% line:89% align:start
without consulting me first.

01:15:47.238 --> 01:15:48.673 position:21% line:89% align:start
Chairman Hang, sir?

01:15:49.674 --> 01:15:52.711 position:13% line:83% align:start
I see no reason for us to
cut our guest's visit short.

01:15:52.744 --> 01:15:54.212 position:19% line:89% align:start
Assign her some guards

01:15:54.245 --> 01:15:56.381 position:24% line:83% align:start
and have them take
her back to her room.

01:15:56.414 --> 01:15:56.915 position:35% line:89% align:start
But, sir!

01:15:56.948 --> 01:15:57.882 position:41% line:83% align:start
[HANG]
Enough!

01:15:57.916 --> 01:15:59.584 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

01:15:59.618 --> 01:16:02.153 position:7% line:83% align:start
[HANG] Truth be told, Colonel,
I have some serious concerns

01:16:02.187 --> 01:16:03.822 position:24% line:83% align:start
about the ways the
Union Military Police

01:16:03.855 --> 01:16:05.091 position:10% line:89% align:start
have been operating lately.

01:16:05.123 --> 01:16:08.893 position:5% line:83% align:start
And the last time I checked, I'm
still the Commander in Chief.

01:16:08.927 --> 01:16:10.395 position:27% line:89% align:start
[NICHOLAS sighs]

01:16:11.596 --> 01:16:12.864 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
Yes, sir.

01:16:20.372 --> 01:16:21.773 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Now, let's see.

01:16:42.894 --> 01:16:43.895 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Mh.

01:17:38.316 --> 01:17:39.317 position:35% line:89% align:start
[knocking]

01:17:40.318 --> 01:17:41.986 position:41% line:83% align:start
[YEO]
Excuse me, Miss Tsunemori.

01:17:42.020 --> 01:17:43.888 position:13% line:83% align:start
I saw that you'd returned,
so I was wondering

01:17:43.922 --> 01:17:46.291 position:21% line:83% align:start
if you wanted me to
make you some lunch?

01:17:48.359 --> 01:17:50.328 position:5% line:89% align:start
Sounds great! Thanks, Miss Yeo.

01:17:50.361 --> 01:17:52.864 position:19% line:83% align:start
I'll eat, right after
my shower's done.

01:17:52.897 --> 01:17:55.433 position:19% line:83% align:start
[YEO] Yes, ma'am. I'll
get started on it now.

01:17:59.804 --> 01:18:02.040 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SHION]
Hm? Akane?

01:18:02.074 --> 01:18:03.942 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Hi, Shion.

01:18:03.975 --> 01:18:04.909 position:27% line:89% align:start
Can you hear me?

01:18:04.943 --> 01:18:07.045 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SHION]
Yeah, loud and clear.

01:18:07.079 --> 01:18:09.814 position:7% line:83% align:start
Looks like the program I gave
you is working out okay.

01:18:09.848 --> 01:18:12.016 position:30% line:89% align:start
So, what's up?

01:18:12.050 --> 01:18:13.685 position:5% line:89% align:start
Is it possible to secretly check

01:18:13.718 --> 01:18:16.321 position:19% line:83% align:start
individual Psycho-Pass
diagnostic devices

01:18:16.354 --> 01:18:18.456 position:19% line:83% align:start
installed in Shambhala
Float, one by one,

01:18:18.490 --> 01:18:20.558 position:16% line:89% align:start
remotely from the MWPSB?

01:18:20.592 --> 01:18:21.259 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SHION]
I guess.

01:18:21.292 --> 01:18:22.894 position:5% line:89% align:start
If we do it via those pill bugs,

01:18:22.927 --> 01:18:24.829 position:21% line:83% align:start
then I don't see why
it wouldn't work.

01:18:24.863 --> 01:18:26.297 position:7% line:89% align:start
But what do you hope to learn?

01:18:26.331 --> 01:18:27.866 position:27% line:83% align:start
The Sibyl System
is in place there

01:18:27.899 --> 01:18:30.835 position:16% line:83% align:start
and should be operating
fine. What's wrong?

01:18:30.869 --> 01:18:32.871 position:13% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] I think that maybe
the system isn't being used

01:18:32.904 --> 01:18:34.839 position:5% line:89% align:start
in a fair and just manner here.

01:18:34.873 --> 01:18:36.875 position:21% line:83% align:start
Look at the ones in
the special district,

01:18:36.908 --> 01:18:39.544 position:19% line:83% align:start
especially around the
Military Police facilities.

01:18:39.577 --> 01:18:42.514 position:13% line:83% align:start
Check to see how accurate
the cymatic scans they do are.

01:18:42.547 --> 01:18:44.749 position:16% line:83% align:start
And let me know as soon
as you find anything.

01:18:47.018 --> 01:18:48.920 position:16% line:89% align:start
"Detective's intuition"?

01:18:50.388 --> 01:18:52.056 position:24% line:83% align:start
No, it's a little
more than that.

01:18:52.091 --> 01:18:54.926 position:16% line:83% align:start
It's a conclusion based
on logical inferences.

01:18:57.562 --> 01:18:59.430 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SHION]
All right. Got it.

01:18:59.464 --> 01:19:01.399 position:16% line:89% align:start
I'll see what I can do.

01:19:01.432 --> 01:19:02.634 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Oh, one more thing.

01:19:02.667 --> 01:19:04.769 position:7% line:83% align:start
You know the collars they use
to monitor latent criminals

01:19:04.803 --> 01:19:07.772 position:27% line:83% align:start
in the Shambhala
Special District?

01:19:07.806 --> 01:19:10.441 position:24% line:83% align:start
Those are made in
Japan, too, right?

01:19:10.475 --> 01:19:12.577 position:13% line:89% align:start
So, under MWPSB clearance,

01:19:12.610 --> 01:19:14.579 position:24% line:83% align:start
can you access the
code to remove one?

01:19:14.612 --> 01:19:15.847 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SHION]
Yeah, no problem.

01:19:15.880 --> 01:19:20.351 position:7% line:83% align:start
But could be bad for you. The
Military Police won't be happy.

01:19:20.385 --> 01:19:23.354 position:7% line:83% align:start
Oh, we are way past the point
of making a difference there.

01:19:23.388 --> 01:19:25.723 position:27% line:83% align:start
Their happiness
doesn't concern me.

01:19:27.025 --> 01:19:29.327 position:21% line:83% align:start
[YEO] Your lunch is
ready, Miss Tsunemori.

01:19:32.397 --> 01:19:33.998 position:16% line:89% align:start
Thanks, it looks great.

01:19:42.540 --> 01:19:43.942 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
Don't say anything.

01:19:43.975 --> 01:19:44.976 position:41% line:83% align:start
[YEO]
Huh?

01:19:48.080 --> 01:19:49.814 position:33% line:89% align:start
[YEO gasps]

01:19:49.848 --> 01:19:51.950 position:41% line:83% align:start
[YEO]
My--But how?

01:19:51.983 --> 01:19:55.053 position:10% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] Please, remain calm
and listen to me carefully.

01:19:55.087 --> 01:19:59.591 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm going to need
your... uh... your help--

01:19:59.624 --> 01:20:00.758 position:33% line:89% align:start
[YEO gasps]

01:20:08.900 --> 01:20:10.768 position:21% line:89% align:start
Looks like this is--

01:20:26.851 --> 01:20:28.052 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SHION]
Hmm...

01:20:30.622 --> 01:20:32.490 position:41% line:83% align:start
[YEO]
I did just as you said!

01:20:32.523 --> 01:20:36.095 position:16% line:83% align:start
You'll really remove my
brother's collar now, won't you?

01:20:36.128 --> 01:20:38.930 position:27% line:83% align:start
You're entirely
too trusting, my dear.

01:20:45.170 --> 01:20:47.906 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE grunts]

01:20:47.939 --> 01:20:49.607 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
Don't kill the girl yet.

01:20:49.641 --> 01:20:52.977 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'll arrange for her to die with
our guerrilla military advisor.

01:20:53.011 --> 01:20:55.880 position:19% line:83% align:start
That should avoid any
unnecessary suspicion.

01:20:58.150 --> 01:21:01.486 position:13% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] So, it seems like
my assumption was correct.

01:21:01.519 --> 01:21:04.455 position:19% line:83% align:start
You aren't even using
the cymatic scans.

01:21:05.623 --> 01:21:07.859 position:19% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] Somehow you're
circumventing them.

01:21:08.960 --> 01:21:10.728 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
Oh?

01:21:10.762 --> 01:21:12.997 position:10% line:89% align:start
And what proof do you have?

01:21:13.031 --> 01:21:16.634 position:16% line:83% align:start
You just killed someone.
That's all the proof I need.

01:21:17.669 --> 01:21:20.738 position:7% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS] If the Sibyl System
raises no objection to it,

01:21:20.772 --> 01:21:22.707 position:7% line:89% align:start
then an action must be legal.

01:21:24.542 --> 01:21:27.112 position:10% line:89% align:start
Isn't that right, Inspector?

01:21:27.146 --> 01:21:29.447 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE grunts]

01:21:36.521 --> 01:21:38.090 position:41% line:83% align:start
[MAN]
Hey, what'd you get me?

01:21:42.627 --> 01:21:43.995 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunts]

01:21:44.028 --> 01:21:52.104 position:24% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI groaning]

01:21:52.137 --> 01:21:53.072 position:24% line:89% align:start
[WEBER chuckkles]

01:21:53.105 --> 01:21:55.107 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunts]

01:21:55.140 --> 01:21:57.976 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI coughs]

01:21:58.009 --> 01:22:00.044 position:38% line:83% align:start
[WEBER]
Hey, did you get it?

01:22:02.046 --> 01:22:05.016 position:16% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI] These aren't...
regular army methods.

01:22:05.049 --> 01:22:06.818 position:13% line:89% align:start
Lemme guess: Mercenaries?

01:22:06.851 --> 01:22:09.053 position:33% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA]
You surprised me.

01:22:09.088 --> 01:22:10.888 position:7% line:89% align:start
The guerrilla military advisor

01:22:10.922 --> 01:22:14.025 position:21% line:83% align:start
we've heard so much
about is Japanese.

01:22:14.058 --> 01:22:16.661 position:10% line:83% align:start
I thought the only soldiers
left in Japan were scum

01:22:16.694 --> 01:22:20.199 position:7% line:83% align:start
who'd had their spines ripped
out by that sham you call Sibyl.

01:22:20.232 --> 01:22:21.666 position:24% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI chuckles]

01:22:21.699 --> 01:22:23.168 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI]
Why do you think I'm here?

01:22:23.202 --> 01:22:25.636 position:21% line:83% align:start
There's no place for
me there anymore.

01:22:29.274 --> 01:22:32.277 position:7% line:83% align:start
So you got training to become
a pro, then left the service?

01:22:32.311 --> 01:22:35.080 position:13% line:83% align:start
Too bad you turned out to
be a pretty lousy mercenary.

01:22:35.114 --> 01:22:37.216 position:24% line:83% align:start
See, you lack the
most important skill,

01:22:37.249 --> 01:22:39.884 position:21% line:83% align:start
which is how to pick
the right employer.

01:22:39.917 --> 01:22:40.952 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI]
Don't try to paint me

01:22:40.985 --> 01:22:43.288 position:24% line:83% align:start
as a bloodthirsty
hyena like you!

01:22:43.322 --> 01:22:46.158 position:7% line:83% align:start
I'm not in this because I get
off on slaughtering people

01:22:46.191 --> 01:22:47.959 position:21% line:83% align:start
like they're nothing
more than animals.

01:22:47.992 --> 01:22:49.228 position:33% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA]
Funny.

01:22:49.261 --> 01:22:53.198 position:5% line:83% align:start
That's the sort of line I'd only
expect from a former detective.

01:22:53.232 --> 01:22:54.732 position:7% line:89% align:start
You wanna slap a pretty label

01:22:54.766 --> 01:22:58.103 position:16% line:83% align:start
like "law" or "justice"
on your violent actions?

01:22:59.904 --> 01:23:00.972 position:33% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA]
In a failed state,

01:23:01.005 --> 01:23:04.076 position:16% line:83% align:start
violence, by necessity,
is privatized.

01:23:04.109 --> 01:23:07.011 position:19% line:83% align:start
Because a monopoly on
organized, systematic violence

01:23:07.045 --> 01:23:09.214 position:10% line:89% align:start
is the essence of a nation.

01:23:10.982 --> 01:23:12.717 position:13% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA] Once violence
spreads everywhere,

01:23:12.750 --> 01:23:15.287 position:24% line:83% align:start
it ceases to serve
a political function.

01:23:16.288 --> 01:23:18.689 position:13% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA] That's when it
becomes an economic engine

01:23:18.723 --> 01:23:22.327 position:19% line:83% align:start
for the state, fueled
by society's rage.

01:23:22.361 --> 01:23:23.561 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunts]

01:23:27.665 --> 01:23:28.900 position:33% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA]
Hm.

01:23:30.102 --> 01:23:31.869 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI groans]

01:23:31.903 --> 01:23:33.704 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI]
The Wretched of the Earth, huh?

01:23:33.738 --> 01:23:36.040 position:19% line:83% align:start
Mercenaries justifying
their actions

01:23:36.075 --> 01:23:39.278 position:7% line:83% align:start
with post-colonial philosophy
are annoying as shit.

01:23:39.311 --> 01:23:40.878 position:24% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI groaning]

01:23:40.912 --> 01:23:44.715 position:19% line:83% align:start
Oh my. A well-trained
and a well-read fighter?

01:23:44.749 --> 01:23:47.051 position:19% line:83% align:start
Now you've really got
my interest piqued.

01:23:47.086 --> 01:23:50.389 position:24% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI groaning]

01:23:50.422 --> 01:23:52.056 position:30% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI yelps]

01:23:52.091 --> 01:23:54.093 position:33% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA]
You know, as I understand it,

01:23:54.126 --> 01:23:55.394 position:33% line:83% align:start
your friends
would've followed you

01:23:55.427 --> 01:23:58.230 position:16% line:83% align:start
all the way to the gates
of Hell and beyond.

01:23:58.263 --> 01:24:00.365 position:21% line:83% align:start
Did you inspire them
with platitudes

01:24:00.399 --> 01:24:02.267 position:27% line:83% align:start
and some kind of
rousing ideology?

01:24:02.301 --> 01:24:04.936 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunts]

01:24:04.969 --> 01:24:06.671 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI groans]

01:24:06.704 --> 01:24:08.273 position:19% line:89% align:start
Who knows what did it.

01:24:08.307 --> 01:24:11.376 position:24% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunting]

01:24:11.410 --> 01:24:14.179 position:5% line:89% align:start
Well, whatever they saw in you.

01:24:14.213 --> 01:24:17.014 position:16% line:83% align:start
I must admit, you've got
something special going on.

01:24:17.048 --> 01:24:19.884 position:16% line:83% align:start
I get a real thrill out
of hearing you talk.

01:24:19.917 --> 01:24:21.752 position:35% line:89% align:start
It's nice.

01:24:21.786 --> 01:24:23.255 position:38% line:89% align:start
[roars]

01:24:23.288 --> 01:24:24.356 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunts]

01:24:25.357 --> 01:24:26.358 position:33% line:89% align:start
[BUN gasps]

01:24:31.996 --> 01:24:33.898 position:24% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI] Thanks, I
appreciate the compliment,

01:24:33.931 --> 01:24:36.868 position:21% line:83% align:start
but it'd sound a lot
better coming from her.

01:24:36.901 --> 01:24:39.371 position:19% line:83% align:start
Just doesn't sound as
sweet coming from you.

01:24:39.404 --> 01:24:42.274 position:24% line:89% align:start
[RUTAGANDA laughs]

01:24:42.307 --> 01:24:44.343 position:13% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA] Learn to show
your elders some respect.

01:24:44.376 --> 01:24:47.379 position:24% line:89% align:start
Insolent bastard!

01:24:47.412 --> 01:24:49.214 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunts]

01:24:50.182 --> 01:24:51.682 position:33% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA]
Still, that talent of yours

01:24:51.716 --> 01:24:53.985 position:21% line:83% align:start
is a valuable thing,
my Japanese friend.

01:24:54.018 --> 01:24:57.122 position:13% line:83% align:start
In fact, you have all the
makings of a great agitator.

01:24:57.156 --> 01:24:59.358 position:21% line:83% align:start
It's a special kind
of charisma you possess

01:24:59.391 --> 01:25:03.262 position:10% line:83% align:start
that can instigate anger and
give purpose to resentment.

01:25:06.365 --> 01:25:08.200 position:33% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA]
Small though it may be...

01:25:09.834 --> 01:25:10.668 position:33% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA]
...we've got our own

01:25:10.701 --> 01:25:13.405 position:30% line:83% align:start
self-governing
community going on here.

01:25:14.739 --> 01:25:15.940 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI groans]

01:25:15.973 --> 01:25:17.476 position:7% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA] And eventually, I
want to gather more soldiers

01:25:17.509 --> 01:25:19.344 position:10% line:89% align:start
and form an army of my own.

01:25:19.378 --> 01:25:22.114 position:16% line:83% align:start
Now, when the time comes
to put that plan into action,

01:25:22.147 --> 01:25:24.449 position:10% line:83% align:start
run-of-the-mill leadership?
That just won't cut it.

01:25:24.483 --> 01:25:25.683 position:24% line:83% align:start
We'll need someone
at the forefront

01:25:25.716 --> 01:25:29.254 position:10% line:83% align:start
who has the power to inspire
a crowd with his gift of gab.

01:25:29.288 --> 01:25:33.858 position:21% line:83% align:start
So. What do ya say?
Will you join us?

01:25:33.891 --> 01:25:36.461 position:19% line:83% align:start
I can help you to hone
that talent of yours,

01:25:36.495 --> 01:25:40.098 position:5% line:83% align:start
and build a platform from which
you can make the most of it.

01:25:41.099 --> 01:25:43.135 position:38% line:83% align:start
[WEBER]
Hey, boss, wait.

01:25:43.168 --> 01:25:45.237 position:10% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA] Bear in mind, if
we hand you over to our client

01:25:45.270 --> 01:25:48.140 position:13% line:83% align:start
like we were hired to do,
it's a certain death sentence.

01:25:48.173 --> 01:25:50.409 position:10% line:83% align:start
You should be grateful that
I'm offering you a reprieve.

01:25:50.442 --> 01:25:52.743 position:5% line:89% align:start
It's your only shot at survival.

01:25:54.112 --> 01:25:56.181 position:24% line:83% align:start
Forgive me for not
bowing at your feet,

01:25:56.215 --> 01:25:59.984 position:13% line:83% align:start
but what you offer, that's
a fate worse than death.

01:26:01.018 --> 01:26:02.454 position:24% line:89% align:start
[RUTAGANDA sighs]

01:26:03.455 --> 01:26:05.790 position:35% line:89% align:start
[ringing]

01:26:05.823 --> 01:26:06.924 position:33% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA]
All right, boys.

01:26:06.958 --> 01:26:08.960 position:7% line:89% align:start
Let's get this guy patched up.

01:26:11.363 --> 01:26:12.763 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
Is he still alive?

01:26:12.797 --> 01:26:13.998 position:27% line:89% align:start
The male target?

01:26:15.032 --> 01:26:17.969 position:7% line:89% align:start
Yeah. So, can I kill him yet?

01:26:18.002 --> 01:26:20.105 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
He still has some use.

01:26:20.138 --> 01:26:22.006 position:27% line:89% align:start
Bring him to me.

01:26:22.039 --> 01:26:24.176 position:33% line:89% align:start
Understood.

01:26:24.209 --> 01:26:25.244 position:21% line:89% align:start
[RUTAGANDA chuckles]

01:26:25.277 --> 01:26:26.545 position:27% line:83% align:start
I wanted to give
you a little while

01:26:26.578 --> 01:26:29.046 position:5% line:89% align:start
to think it over, but, oh well.

01:26:29.081 --> 01:26:31.250 position:24% line:83% align:start
Chalk it up to bad
timing, I guess.

01:26:31.283 --> 01:26:32.850 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunts]

01:27:13.991 --> 01:27:16.128 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI groans]

01:27:16.161 --> 01:27:17.496 position:38% line:89% align:start
Kogami.

01:27:19.331 --> 01:27:21.433 position:7% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS] "During transport,
the Japanese terrorist

01:27:21.466 --> 01:27:23.435 position:13% line:83% align:start
who'd aided the guerrillas
lashed out violently,

01:27:23.468 --> 01:27:25.304 position:27% line:83% align:start
taking Inspector
Tsunemori hostage

01:27:25.337 --> 01:27:27.472 position:10% line:89% align:start
and hijacking a helicopter.

01:27:27.506 --> 01:27:30.509 position:13% line:83% align:start
Because we feared he would
target government facilities,

01:27:30.542 --> 01:27:32.444 position:7% line:89% align:start
we regrettably had no choice.

01:27:32.477 --> 01:27:34.912 position:21% line:83% align:start
We shot them down to
take out the threat."

01:27:34.945 --> 01:27:37.449 position:5% line:89% align:start
That's the story we'll present.

01:27:37.482 --> 01:27:38.550 position:33% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA]
Seems like a waste

01:27:38.583 --> 01:27:42.587 position:10% line:83% align:start
of a perfectly good chopper
just to off two people.

01:27:42.621 --> 01:27:46.191 position:16% line:83% align:start
Well, if it's the fault
of an MWPSB Inspector,

01:27:46.224 --> 01:27:48.859 position:16% line:83% align:start
we can stick Japan with
the bill for a new one.

01:27:49.661 --> 01:27:51.630 position:30% line:83% align:start
I'd like this
taken care of quickly.

01:27:51.663 --> 01:27:52.764 position:24% line:89% align:start
All we really need

01:27:52.798 --> 01:27:55.600 position:19% line:83% align:start
is to be able to find
their bodies in the wreckage.

01:27:56.601 --> 01:27:59.404 position:19% line:89% align:start
So, execute them now.

01:27:59.438 --> 01:28:03.342 position:27% line:89% align:start
[AKANE grunting]

01:28:03.375 --> 01:28:06.244 position:24% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI groaning]

01:28:12.317 --> 01:28:13.918 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
You should know this won't work.

01:28:13.951 --> 01:28:16.321 position:5% line:89% align:start
It's way too obvious a cover up!

01:28:16.355 --> 01:28:19.458 position:13% line:83% align:start
How gullible do you think
Chairman Hang is?

01:28:19.491 --> 01:28:20.559 position:30% line:89% align:start
The Chairman?

01:28:20.592 --> 01:28:23.128 position:16% line:83% align:start
Tthe Japanese government
won't take this lying down!

01:28:23.161 --> 01:28:24.061 position:13% line:89% align:start
They're gonna investigate

01:28:24.096 --> 01:28:26.665 position:24% line:83% align:start
and find out what
really happened here!

01:28:26.698 --> 01:28:29.167 position:24% line:83% align:start
What a sad little
bureaucratic pawn.

01:28:29.201 --> 01:28:30.202 position:13% line:89% align:start
She could never figure out

01:28:30.235 --> 01:28:32.404 position:13% line:83% align:start
what her master was doing
with his right hand.

01:28:32.437 --> 01:28:35.340 position:19% line:83% align:start
While the entire time
she was moved by his left.

01:28:35.374 --> 01:28:37.476 position:27% line:83% align:start
Miss Tsunemori,
how would you feel

01:28:37.509 --> 01:28:38.744 position:30% line:83% align:start
if we told you
everything we're doing

01:28:38.777 --> 01:28:41.613 position:7% line:83% align:start
is in complete accordance with
your government's directives?

01:28:41.646 --> 01:28:42.514 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE gasps]

01:28:42.547 --> 01:28:44.549 position:33% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA]
Isn't that right, Colonel?

01:28:44.583 --> 01:28:47.386 position:19% line:83% align:start
After we assassinated
Hang at your request,

01:28:47.419 --> 01:28:51.323 position:7% line:83% align:start
I hear it was the Japanese who
provided his doppelgänger.

01:28:51.356 --> 01:28:52.290 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE sighs]

01:28:52.324 --> 01:28:53.358 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
Hey!

01:28:53.392 --> 01:28:56.261 position:13% line:83% align:start
That's enough, mercenary,
keep your mouth shut!

01:28:58.130 --> 01:28:59.297 position:27% line:89% align:start
Shoot them, now!

01:28:59.331 --> 01:29:00.332 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE grunts]

01:29:02.634 --> 01:29:03.635 position:38% line:89% align:start
[yelps]

01:29:08.038 --> 01:29:09.907 position:33% line:89% align:start
[BUN grunts]

01:29:14.746 --> 01:29:18.683 position:30% line:89% align:start
[BUN groaning]

01:29:18.717 --> 01:29:20.352 position:24% line:89% align:start
The hell is this?

01:29:20.385 --> 01:29:22.052 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
It's not me!

01:29:22.087 --> 01:29:24.122 position:7% line:83% align:start
[KOMISSA] This is the Criminal
Investigation Department

01:29:24.156 --> 01:29:26.091 position:10% line:89% align:start
of the Public Safety Bureau.

01:29:26.124 --> 01:29:27.526 position:5% line:89% align:start
Under the authority vested in us

01:29:27.559 --> 01:29:30.995 position:13% line:83% align:start
by Sections Three and Five
of the Sibyl System Treaty,

01:29:31.028 --> 01:29:33.030 position:16% line:83% align:start
the Japanese government
has assumed control

01:29:33.064 --> 01:29:35.167 position:13% line:89% align:start
of all security protocols.

01:29:35.200 --> 01:29:38.370 position:13% line:83% align:start
If your Crime Coefficient
exceeds the acceptable value,

01:29:38.403 --> 01:29:40.539 position:19% line:83% align:start
you may be eliminated
without warning.

01:29:40.572 --> 01:29:43.074 position:24% line:83% align:start
It is recommended
that you not resist.

01:29:43.108 --> 01:29:46.344 position:5% line:83% align:start
Please calm yourself so that you
will be mentally stabilized.

01:29:46.378 --> 01:29:48.246 position:7% line:89% align:start
This message will now repeat.

01:29:48.280 --> 01:29:50.348 position:21% line:83% align:start
This is the Criminal
Investigation Department

01:29:50.382 --> 01:29:52.250 position:10% line:89% align:start
of the Public Safety Bureau.

01:29:52.284 --> 01:29:53.218 position:7% line:89% align:start
Under the authority vested...

01:29:53.251 --> 01:29:55.353 position:16% line:89% align:start
Is Japan is taking over?

01:29:56.354 --> 01:29:58.290 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NICHOLAS]
You know nothing about us!

01:29:58.323 --> 01:30:00.759 position:33% line:89% align:start
Interlopers!

01:30:00.792 --> 01:30:03.628 position:33% line:83% align:start
[DOMINATOR]
Crime Coefficient, over 380.

01:30:03.662 --> 01:30:06.598 position:24% line:83% align:start
Enforcement mode:
Lethal Eliminator.

01:30:09.100 --> 01:30:10.435 position:24% line:89% align:start
[NICHOLAS grunts]

01:30:10.469 --> 01:30:11.236 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE yelps]

01:30:11.269 --> 01:30:12.270 position:24% line:89% align:start
[NICHOLAS grunts]

01:30:13.638 --> 01:30:14.639 position:30% line:89% align:start
[AKANE gasps]

