01:31:59.844 --> 01:32:03.448 position:13% line:83% align:start
The scanners in this city.
They were illegally altered.

01:32:03.481 --> 01:32:06.084 position:21% line:83% align:start
This place is a nest
of latent criminals.

01:32:07.152 --> 01:32:09.487 position:27% line:83% align:start
So, how exactly
did they pull it off?

01:32:09.521 --> 01:32:11.156 position:24% line:83% align:start
The Identification
Friend or Foe

01:32:11.189 --> 01:32:13.692 position:16% line:83% align:start
that was originally used
by the SEAUn military.

01:32:13.725 --> 01:32:16.161 position:27% line:83% align:start
They embedded it
in the Hue scan.

01:32:16.194 --> 01:32:19.130 position:27% line:83% align:start
Once somebody's
designated as friendly,

01:32:19.164 --> 01:32:21.399 position:5% line:89% align:start
he's no longer subject to scans.

01:32:21.433 --> 01:32:24.369 position:16% line:83% align:start
And so, as it turns out,
almost every MP officer

01:32:24.402 --> 01:32:27.238 position:16% line:83% align:start
was using this loophole
to fake his Psycho-Pass.

01:32:27.272 --> 01:32:29.474 position:13% line:83% align:start
They could really deceive
the Sibyl System?

01:32:29.507 --> 01:32:31.776 position:24% line:83% align:start
And they did it in
such an obvious way.

01:32:31.810 --> 01:32:34.479 position:10% line:83% align:start
[MIKA] What makes you think
they were deceiving Sibyl?

01:32:34.512 --> 01:32:37.415 position:27% line:83% align:start
It was purposely
overlooked to set this trap.

01:32:37.449 --> 01:32:39.684 position:10% line:83% align:start
From the start, Sibyl's aim
was the wholesale prosecution

01:32:39.718 --> 01:32:41.620 position:33% line:83% align:start
of the Union
Military Police.

01:32:41.653 --> 01:32:43.622 position:13% line:89% align:start
If you had realized that,

01:32:43.655 --> 01:32:46.257 position:13% line:83% align:start
maybe we wouldn't have had
to go through all this trouble.

01:32:46.291 --> 01:32:48.193 position:30% line:83% align:start
You always do
everything the hard way.

01:32:48.226 --> 01:32:49.728 position:19% line:89% align:start
Don't you, Inspector?

01:32:49.761 --> 01:32:51.563 position:24% line:89% align:start
What do you mean?

01:32:51.596 --> 01:32:52.931 position:16% line:83% align:start
[MIKA] People like them
are so easy to read

01:32:52.964 --> 01:32:54.899 position:16% line:83% align:start
that you shouldn't even
need a cymatic scan

01:32:54.933 --> 01:32:56.635 position:7% line:89% align:start
to know what they're thinking.

01:32:56.668 --> 01:32:58.436 position:27% line:83% align:start
Still, until the
infrastructure was in place

01:32:58.470 --> 01:33:00.872 position:21% line:83% align:start
and ready to operate
the system in SEAUn,

01:33:00.905 --> 01:33:03.441 position:24% line:83% align:start
utilizing them was
the only option.

01:33:03.475 --> 01:33:05.276 position:24% line:83% align:start
But once Shambhala
Float gets completed,

01:33:05.310 --> 01:33:07.946 position:16% line:83% align:start
their usefulness begins
to wear off pretty quickly.

01:33:07.979 --> 01:33:09.514 position:21% line:83% align:start
And all that's left
is to gather proof

01:33:09.547 --> 01:33:12.283 position:27% line:83% align:start
of their devious
scheme and crush them.

01:33:12.317 --> 01:33:14.185 position:24% line:83% align:start
See, tracking down
a fugitive Enforcer

01:33:14.219 --> 01:33:16.521 position:27% line:83% align:start
that was just a
pretext to send you in.

01:33:18.823 --> 01:33:20.625 position:38% line:83% align:start
[AKANE]
So, what?

01:33:20.659 --> 01:33:22.827 position:10% line:89% align:start
You're just okay with that?

01:33:22.861 --> 01:33:25.830 position:19% line:83% align:start
Hey, "what needs to be
done is done by those capable."

01:33:25.864 --> 01:33:29.968 position:16% line:83% align:start
But I know not everybody
is capable, Inspector.

01:33:30.001 --> 01:33:31.403 position:35% line:89% align:start
[stammers]

01:33:33.972 --> 01:33:35.407 position:16% line:89% align:start
All right, in that case,

01:33:35.440 --> 01:33:37.742 position:27% line:83% align:start
let's go do what
needs to be done.

01:33:42.414 --> 01:33:45.617 position:5% line:83% align:start
[DOMINATOR] Activating Dominator
Portable Psychological Diagnosis

01:33:45.650 --> 01:33:47.519 position:16% line:89% align:start
and Suppression System.

01:33:47.552 --> 01:33:51.523 position:21% line:83% align:start
User authentication,
Inspector Akane Tsunemori.

01:33:51.556 --> 01:33:53.491 position:19% line:89% align:start
You are a valid user.

01:33:54.592 --> 01:33:58.897 position:13% line:83% align:start
Inspector Shimotsuki, take
Sugo, Kunizuka, and Hinakawa

01:33:58.930 --> 01:34:00.965 position:5% line:89% align:start
and control the situation here.

01:34:00.999 --> 01:34:02.033 position:41% line:89% align:start
Right.

01:34:02.068 --> 01:34:04.903 position:13% line:83% align:start
[AKANE] I'll go bring the
Chairman into custody.

01:34:04.936 --> 01:34:06.838 position:7% line:89% align:start
Ginoza, you're coming with me.

01:34:06.871 --> 01:34:07.972 position:30% line:89% align:start
Lead the way.

01:34:14.345 --> 01:34:20.351 position:24% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI groaning]

01:34:24.889 --> 01:34:28.426 position:21% line:89% align:start
[groaning continues]

01:34:30.929 --> 01:34:32.731 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI groans]

01:34:38.603 --> 01:34:41.272 position:13% line:83% align:start
[MAKISHIMA] This is hardly
the time to play hero.

01:34:41.306 --> 01:34:42.340 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI groans]

01:34:42.373 --> 01:34:43.341 position:19% line:83% align:start
[MAKISHIMA] You should
get out of here yourself.

01:34:43.374 --> 01:34:45.944 position:16% line:83% align:start
Otherwise, you'll be the
one who winds up caught.

01:34:50.682 --> 01:34:53.952 position:10% line:83% align:start
So that's it. The compulsion
is too strong, right?

01:34:53.985 --> 01:34:57.856 position:13% line:83% align:start
You see prey running away
and you have to chase.

01:34:57.889 --> 01:34:59.791 position:30% line:89% align:start
How pathetic.

01:34:59.824 --> 01:35:04.028 position:10% line:83% align:start
At your core, you really are
nothing more than a hunting dog.

01:35:04.062 --> 01:35:05.897 position:19% line:83% align:start
I can't just let a man
who's trying to build up

01:35:05.930 --> 01:35:09.734 position:19% line:83% align:start
his own army get away!
It's far too dangerous!

01:35:09.768 --> 01:35:12.604 position:19% line:83% align:start
That guy's a joke and
his plan is all bluster.

01:35:12.637 --> 01:35:14.906 position:24% line:83% align:start
You shouldn't take
him seriously.

01:35:14.939 --> 01:35:17.542 position:21% line:83% align:start
Besides, he'll crash
and burn on his own.

01:35:21.746 --> 01:35:23.581 position:30% line:83% align:start
What makes you
so determined?

01:35:23.615 --> 01:35:29.454 position:10% line:83% align:start
Some noble sense of justice?
Is that it? I think not.

01:35:29.487 --> 01:35:32.524 position:13% line:83% align:start
There are a lot of people
like Rutaganda in this world.

01:35:32.557 --> 01:35:35.293 position:19% line:83% align:start
Killing him won't make
the slightest difference.

01:35:36.895 --> 01:35:39.063 position:21% line:83% align:start
[MAKISHIMA] And yet
still, you pursue him,

01:35:39.098 --> 01:35:41.100 position:7% line:89% align:start
putting your own life at risk.

01:35:41.133 --> 01:35:43.802 position:30% line:83% align:start
Why are you so
obsessed with this one?

01:35:43.835 --> 01:35:45.970 position:19% line:83% align:start
I thought killing you
would shut you up!

01:35:52.043 --> 01:35:53.311 position:27% line:89% align:start
[KOGAMI grunts]

01:36:03.822 --> 01:36:06.658 position:21% line:83% align:start
From here on. I have
to do this on my own.

01:36:06.691 --> 01:36:08.059 position:27% line:89% align:start
And why is that?

01:36:08.093 --> 01:36:11.096 position:24% line:83% align:start
Follow orders and
track down Kogami.

01:36:12.664 --> 01:36:14.066 position:21% line:89% align:start
Do I have free rein?

01:36:14.099 --> 01:36:17.702 position:10% line:83% align:start
To handle him how I see fit,
at my own discretion?

01:36:17.735 --> 01:36:19.071 position:27% line:89% align:start
It's up to you.

01:36:33.685 --> 01:36:36.454 position:7% line:83% align:start
[RUTAGANDA] You're not really
a detective, are you?

01:36:36.487 --> 01:36:37.856 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KOGAMI]
I'm retired.

01:36:39.891 --> 01:36:42.427 position:10% line:89% align:start
Didn't mean your job title.

01:36:42.460 --> 01:36:46.030 position:10% line:83% align:start
I was talking about the way
you act. Your very nature.

01:36:46.065 --> 01:36:47.066 position:24% line:89% align:start
[RUTAGANDA grunts]

01:36:52.670 --> 01:36:54.505 position:24% line:89% align:start
[RUTAGANDA grunts]

